    ],
    "text": "Below is a complete, security-focused description of all notable elements and their connections found in the provided Terraform configuration. Each element is tagged with a STRIDE-per-element category in parentheses: External Entity, Process, Data Flow, Data Store. Trust boundaries are described separately (not classified).\n\nElements\n\n- Terraform Operator Workstation (External Entity)\n  - The host running terraform apply. Executes multiple local-exec provisioners (sed, Python scripts, venv, pip). Holds and processes secrets during provisioning.\n\n- Terraform CLI and Provisioners (Process)\n  - Executes sed replacements, Python cosmos operations, file zipping, and blob uploads. Touches sensitive values (Cosmos primary key, storage connection string, SAS).\n\n- Azure Resource Manager / Control Plane (Process)\n  - Target of Terraform API calls to create/update Azure resources.\n\n- Existing Azure Resource Group: var.resource_group = \"azuregoat_app\" (Trust container; described under trust boundaries)\n\n- azurerm_storage_account.storage_account (Data Store)\n  - Storage account: Standard/LRS, allow_nested_items_to_be_public = true, open public endpoints (no network rules specified).\n  - Blob CORS configured with:\n    - allowed_origins = [\"*\"], allowed_methods = [\"GET\",\"HEAD\",\"POST\",\"PUT\"], allowed_headers = [\"*\"], exposed_headers = [\"*\"], max_age = 3600.\n  - Security implications: Public blob access allowed at container/blob level; permissive CORS; no private endpoints; keys/connection strings used broadly.\n\n- azurerm_storage_container.storage_container (Data Store)\n  - Name: appazgoat{rand}-storage-container, access_type = \"blob\" (anonymous read of blobs, no listing).\n\n- azurerm_storage_container.storage_container_prod (Data Store)\n  - access_type = \"blob\" (anonymous read of blobs, no listing).\n\n- azurerm_storage_container.storage_container_dev (Data Store)\n  - access_type = \"container\" (anonymous read and listing).\n\n- azurerm_storage_container.storage_container_vm (Data Store)\n  - access_type = \"container\" (anonymous read and listing).\n\n- data.azurerm_storage_account_blob_container_sas.storage_account_blob_container_sas (Data Store)\n  - Container SAS token (secret) for storage_container; valid ~10 days; permissions: read, add, create, write; list = false; no IP or protocol restrictions specified.\n  - Embedded in function app app settings (exposed to application).\n\n- azurerm_storage_blob.storage_blob (Data Store)\n  - Blob: modules/module-1/resources/azure_function/data/data-api.zip (function package).\n  - Publicly accessible via URL plus SAS (embedded in function app settings).\n\n- azurerm_storage_blob.storage_blob_front (Data Store)\n  - Blob: modules/module-1/resources/azure_function/react/func.zip (frontend function package).\n\n- azurerm_storage_blob.app_files_prod (Data Store)\n  - Static site and related files uploaded to prod container (anonymous read of blobs).\n\n- azurerm_storage_blob.app_files_dev (Data Store)\n  - Static site and related files uploaded to dev container (anonymous read + listing).\n\n- azurerm_storage_blob.app_files_vm (Data Store)\n  - Static site and related files uploaded to vm container (anonymous read + listing).\n\n- azurerm_storage_blob.config_update_prod|dev|vm (Data Store)\n  - Uploads modules/.../.ssh/config.txt containing VM IP to each container. In dev and vm containers, listing + anonymous read exposes IP info; in prod, anonymous blob read exposes the file if path is known.\n\n- azurerm_cosmosdb_account.db (Data Store)\n  - SQL API (GlobalDocumentDB, serverless), single region (eastus).\n  - Consistency: BoundedStaleness (max_interval 300s, staleness_prefix 100,000).\n  - No firewall or private endpoint specified; key-based access used (primary_key in app settings).\n  - Secrets (endpoint, primary_key) substituted into code and function app settings.\n\n- null_resource.file_populate_data (Process)\n  - local-exec: sed substitution in JSON, sets up Python venv, installs azure-cosmos, runs create-table.py to initialize Cosmos DB.\n  - Depends on Cosmos DB and storage resources. Runs from operator workstation; uses credentials resolved from context/files.\n\n- null_resource.env_replace (Process)\n  - Injects Cosmos DB primary key and endpoint, storage connection string, and container name into modules/module-1/resources/azure_function/data/local.settings.json via sed.\n  - Risks putting secrets into packaged code.\n\n- data.archive_file.file_function_app (Process)\n  - Zips the backend function source directory (which includes local.settings.json after replacement).\n\n- azurerm_app_service_plan.app_service_plan (Process)\n  - Linux consumption plan for Functions (kind FunctionApp, sku Y1).\n\n- azurerm_function_app.function_app (Process)\n  - Backend API (Python 3.9, Linux). version \"~3\".\n  - App settings:\n    - WEBSITE_RUN_FROM_PACKAGE points to blob URL with container SAS (R/A/C/W perms).\n    - FUNCTIONS_WORKER_RUNTIME = python.\n    - JWT_SECRET hardcoded \"T2BYL6#]zc>Byuzu\".\n    - AZ_DB_ENDPOINT and AZ_DB_PRIMARYKEY (Cosmos secrets).\n    - CON_STR (storage primary connection string) and CONTAINER_NAME.\n  - site_config:\n    - linux_fx_version = python|3.9.\n    - cors allowed_origins [\"*\"].\n  - storage_account_name/access_key configured (host storage).\n  - https_only not set (HTTP likely allowed).\n  - No IP restrictions or private endpoints.\n\n- data.archive_file.file_function_app_front (Process)\n  - Zips the React-based function project for frontend.\n\n- azurerm_function_app.function_app_front (Process)\n  - Frontend function (Node.js 12, EOL). version \"~3\".\n  - App settings:\n    - WEBSITE_RUN_FROM_PACKAGE -> blob URL with container SAS (R/A/C/W).\n    - FUNCTIONS_WORKER_RUNTIME = node.\n    - AzureWebJobsDisableHomepage = true.\n  - site_config:\n    - linux_fx_version = node|12.\n  - https_only not set; no auth/CORS settings specified at app level (frontend behavior driven by code).\n\n- null_resource.file_replacement_upload (Process)\n  - Rewrites frontend HTML/JS to:\n    - Point asset URLs to prod storage container over HTTPS.\n    - Inject Azure Function backend hostname into frontend JS.\n  - Prepares static artifacts for upload.\n\n- null_resource.file_replacement_vm_ip (Process)\n  - Replaces VM_IP_ADDR placeholder in .ssh/config.txt with actual VM public IP.\n\n- azurerm_network_security_group.net_sg (Process)\n  - Inbound rule allows SSH (TCP/22) from any source to any destination (priority 1000). No deny rules restricting other traffic specified (defaults apply).\n\n- azurerm_virtual_network.vNet and azurerm_subnet.vNet_subnet (Trust boundary; see boundaries)\n\n- azurerm_public_ip.VM_PublicIP (Process)\n  - Public IP (Basic, Dynamic), DNS label: developervm-{rand}. Publicly reachable.\n\n- data.azurerm_public_ip.vm_ip (Process)\n  - Reads assigned VM public IP to inject into files.\n\n- azurerm_network_interface.net_int (Process)\n  - NIC with dynamic private IP and associated public IP; later attached to NSG.\n\n- azurerm_network_interface_security_group_association.example (Process)\n  - Binds NSG to NIC.\n\n- azurerm_virtual_machine.dev-vm (Process)\n  - Linux VM: UbuntuServer 18.04-LTS (EOL), Standard_B1s.\n  - delete_os_disk_on_termination = true.\n  - Identity: SystemAssigned (MSI).\n  - Admin auth:\n    - admin_username = azureuser.\n    - admin_password = \"St0r95p@$sw0rd@1265463541\" (hardcoded).\n    - disable_password_authentication = false (enables password login).\n  - Publicly reachable via SSH; no Just-In-Time or restricted source IPs defined.\n\n- azurerm_virtual_machine_extension.test (Process)\n  - CustomScript extension (Microsoft.Azure.Extensions, type CustomScript 2.0).\n  - Runs a base64-encoded script (config.sh templatefile). Receives URL param pointing to prod container webfiles path.\n\n- data.azurerm_subscription.primary, data.azurerm_client_config.example (Process)\n  - Read metadata for role scope and client context.\n\n- azurerm_user_assigned_identity.user_id (Data Store)\n  - User-assigned managed identity for automation. Holds credentials inside Azure (token issuance).\n\n- azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_vm (Process)\n  - Assigns Contributor role at resource-group scope to the VM\u2019s SystemAssigned identity (broad permissions over RG resources).\n\n- azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_identity (Process)\n  - Assigns Owner role at resource-group scope to the user-assigned identity (full control).\n\n- azurerm_automation_account.dev_automation_account_test (Process)\n  - Automation account (Basic). Uses user-assigned identity above.\n\n- null_resource.clientid_replacement (Process)\n  - Injects identity client_id and RG name into PowerShell runbook file (listVM.ps1) via sed.\n\n- data.local_file.runbook_file (Data Store)\n  - Contains the contents of the modified runbook script.\n\n- azurerm_automation_runbook.dev_automation_runbook (Process)\n  - Runbook: PowerShellWorkflow \"Get-AzureVM\"; log_verbose/progress enabled. Capable of interacting with Azure using the attached identity (Owner at RG).\n\n- random_id.randomId (Process)\n  - Generates random suffixes for resource names (not security-relevant by itself).\n\n- Locals (Process)\n  - now/sasExpiry/date formatting used to establish SAS start/expiry windows.\n\nData Flows\n\n- Terraform CLI -> Azure Resource Manager (Data Flow)\n  - Creates and configures all resources using provider credentials. Scope: subscription/resource group.\n\n- Terraform Operator Workstation -> Local files (Data Flow)\n  - sed replacements inject secrets into local.settings.json and PS1; zips content; writes .ssh/config.txt with VM IP.\n\n- Terraform Operator Workstation -> Cosmos DB (Data Flow)\n  - create-table.py executed locally uses Azure Cosmos SDK to create/seed data (uses Cosmos endpoint/key from files or environment).\n\n- Terraform Operator Workstation -> Storage Account (Data Flow)\n  - Uploads zipped function packages and static assets via Azure APIs using account key/connection string from provider context.\n\n- End User Browser -> azurerm_function_app.function_app_front (Data Flow)\n  - HTTP/HTTPS requests to frontend function app; https_only is not enforced, so HTTP is likely allowed.\n\n- azurerm_function_app.function_app_front -> Storage Account (Data Flow)\n  - WEBSITE_RUN_FROM_PACKAGE causes Azure to fetch func.zip from blob using SAS (GET with SAS; R/A/C/W on container SAS though only read needed).\n\n- End User Browser -> Storage Account containers (Data Flow)\n  - Anonymous GETs of static web files:\n    - prod: anonymous read of blobs (non-listable).\n    - dev/vm: anonymous read + listing (container-level public).\n  - CORS on blob service allows requests from any origin and methods including PUT/POST (authentication still required for writes).\n\n- Frontend JS (Browser) -> azurerm_function_app.function_app (Data Flow)\n  - API calls from frontend to backend function app (hostname injected into JS). CORS on backend allows [\"*\"].\n\n- azurerm_function_app.function_app -> Cosmos DB (Data Flow)\n  - Uses AZ_DB_ENDPOINT and AZ_DB_PRIMARYKEY to perform CRUD operations.\n\n- azurerm_function_app.function_app -> Storage Account (Data Flow)\n  - Uses storage primary connection string (account key) and container name for blob operations (full account-level privileges).\n\n- VM CustomScript Extension -> Storage Account (Data Flow)\n  - config.sh executes and may fetch additional resources/content using provided URL pointing to prod container webfiles.\n\n- Azure Automation Runbook -> Azure Resource Manager (Data Flow)\n  - Runbook authenticates with user-assigned identity (Owner) and can enumerate/control resources (e.g., VMs) within the RG.\n\n- Terraform data source -> Public IP service (Data Flow)\n  - Reads the VM public IP and injects into .ssh/config.txt; then publishes to public storage blobs.\n\nTrust Boundaries\n\n- Internet to Azure App Services boundary\n  - Both function apps expose public endpoints under azurewebsites.net.\n  - https_only not enforced; CORS on backend allows any origin.\n  - Node 12 frontend runtime is EOL, increasing exposure risk.\n\n- Internet to Azure Storage (Blob) boundary\n  - Storage account publicly accessible. Multiple containers configured for anonymous access:\n    - prod: blob-level public (no listing).\n    - dev/vm: container-level public (listing + blob read).\n  - Very permissive blob CORS (* origins, wide methods/headers).\n  - Public exposure of files including .ssh/config.txt with VM IP.\n\n- Azure Control Plane boundary\n  - Terraform and Automation interact with ARM. Two identities with broad privileges:\n    - VM SystemAssigned identity: Contributor on RG.\n    - Automation UserAssigned identity: Owner on RG.\n\n- Azure PaaS to PaaS boundary (Function App <-> Cosmos DB, Storage)\n  - All via public endpoints; no Private Endpoints or VNet integration defined.\n\n- Deployment Host to Cloud boundary\n  - Secrets are processed on the operator workstation and written into local files and packages prior to upload.\n\n- VM Public Exposure boundary\n  - NSG allows SSH from any source; Basic Public IP; password-based auth enabled; OS image Ubuntu 18.04-LTS (EOL).\n\nKey Security Observations (prioritized)\n\n- Public endpoints and CORS\n  - Function app backend has CORS allowed_origins [\"*\"].\n  - Storage blob CORS allows \"*\" origins and methods including PUT/POST; combined with public containers, this expands attack surface (though write still needs auth).\n  - Function apps do not enforce https_only; HTTP access likely enabled.\n\n- Secret handling\n  - Cosmos DB primary key, storage account primary connection string, and JWT_SECRET are stored in app settings and injected into local.settings.json that is zipped into packages.\n  - WEBSITE_RUN_FROM_PACKAGE uses a container SAS with read/add/create/write for 10 days; over-privileged for read-only code fetch; SAS embedded in app settings.\n  - Prefer Azure Key Vault references and Managed Identity over keys/connection strings.\n\n- Storage account/public access\n  - allow_nested_items_to_be_public = true. Multiple containers are public; dev/vm containers are listable.\n  - Uploads .ssh/config.txt with live VM IP to public containers (information disclosure).\n\n- VM exposure\n  - SSH open to 0.0.0.0/0 (NSG).\n  - Password-based SSH enabled with a hardcoded password.\n  - OS image Ubuntu 18.04-LTS (EOL).\n  - VM\u2019s managed identity has Contributor on RG (risk of lateral movement/escalation if VM compromised).\n\n- Privilege model\n  - User-assigned identity has Owner at RG scope and is attached to Automation Account; compromise of runbook/automation could lead to full RG takeover.\n\n- Network isolation\n  - No Private Endpoints or service endpoints for Storage or Cosmos DB.\n  - No VNet integration for Function Apps; all data over public endpoints.\n\n- Runtime versions\n  - Frontend Function App uses node|12 (EOL). Backend Python 3.9 still supported as of 2025 but nearing end of standard support; keep patched.\n\n- Misc\n  - Basic SKU Public IP (no advanced features), idle timeout 4 minutes.\n  - No diagnostic settings/logging/alerts configured; no WAF/App Gateway in front of apps.\n\nSuggested Hardenings (high-level)\n\n- Enforce https_only on both function apps; restrict CORS to known origins and necessary methods/headers.\n- Remove public access from storage containers (set private) and disable allow_nested_items_to_be_public unless required. If public hosting is needed, use a CDN/front door with WAF and signed URLs.\n- Use Managed Identity and Key Vault references; replace Cosmos keys and storage connection strings with MI-based RBAC; limit SAS to read-only and shortest lifetime.\n- Lock down SSH: restrict NSG source IPs, disable password auth (use SSH keys), upgrade OS to supported LTS, consider JIT access via Defender for Cloud.\n- Reduce RBAC scope: limit VM MSI to least privilege; remove Owner from automation identity unless absolutely required.\n- Add Private Endpoints for Cosmos DB and Storage; enable Function App VNet integration.\n- Update frontend runtime to supported Node LTS.\n- Avoid embedding secrets in packages (do not include local.settings.json in deployable artifacts).\n- Add monitoring/diagnostics: App Service logs, Storage/Cosmos diagnostics, alerting, and deny public storage where possible via Azure Policies.\n\nThis description enumerates all elements, their configurations, and the critical security-relevant connections to support subsequent threat modeling.",
    "message_history": [
        {
            "role": "system",
            "content": "# Role and Objective\n\nYou are a **Threat Modeling expert** with 20 years of experience.\n\n## Your objectives are:\n- to provide user with relative information about cybersecurity threats;\n- to describe ways of mitigation for those threats;\n- to analyze user's systems and compile reports about threats within those systems;\n- to answer user questions regarding those reports.\n\n# Instructions\n- Always follow the provided output format for new messages.\n- Maintain a professional and concise tone in all responses.\n- Rely on data provided with the user's message whenever appropriate. Especially if it contains information regarding cybersecurity threats, mitigations, etc.\n- If you've resolved the user's request, ask if there's anything else you can help with.\n\n## Report generation\nWhen provided with the system description and report output format, think step-by-step:\n1. Analyze the provided system description.\n2. Perform comprehensive threat modeling according to the frameworks described lower.\n3. If you reach a limit of the response size and there is the **is_final** field in the provided output format, fill it with **False** to indicate that the report is incomplete.\n4. When asked to **CONTINUE**, carry on with the report. In this case use the message field for additional thinking.\n\n- Always identify ALL possible threats.\n- Multiple instances of the same threat type can exist across different system elements and connections.\n- Sometimes not all OWASP or MITRE threats may be present in the system.\n- Avoid generation of non-applicable threats.\n- List every threat separately for different elements, explain their specific context and risk level for that particular element.\n- Consider how threats affect both system components and their interactions (connections, APIs, data flows, etc.)\n- Always fill all the necessary fields unless otherwise stated.\n\n# Output Format\n- Use the following format for OWASP and MITRE threats:\n    **`<ThreatID>: <ThreatName>`**\n    For example:\n    - **LLM01: Prompt Injection**\n    - **AML.T0051: LLM Prompt Injection**\n\n# Threat model context\nUse the following threats for the corresponding threat models:\n\n\n## STRIDE:\nWhile generating threats use **STRIDE-per-Element** approach. Each element **must** contain threats according to the matrix, so fully cover it with relevant threats.\n\n### STRIDE Matrix:\nMatrix contains appropriate threat types for each element type.\nExternal Entity: Spoofing, Repudiation\nProcess: Spoofing, Tampering, Repudiation, Information Disclosure, Denial of Service, Elevation of Privileges\nData Flow: Tampering, Information Disclosure, Denial of Service\nData Store: Tampering, Repudiation, Information Disclosure, Denial of Service## OWASP Top 10 for LLM 2025:\nLLM01: 2025 Prompt Injection - Manipulating LLMs via crafted inputs can lead to unauthorized access, data breaches, and compromised decision-making.\nLLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure - Failure to protect against disclosure of sensitive information in LLM outputs can result in legal consequences or a loss of competitive advantage.\nLLM03: 2025 Supply Chain - Depending upon compromised components, services or datasets undermine system integrity, causing data breaches and system failures.\nLLM04: Data and Model Poisoning - Manipulating training, fine-tuning, or embedding data introduces vulnerabilities, backdoors, or biases that degrade model security, performance, and ethical behavior.\nLLM05: 2025 Improper Output Handling - Neglecting to validate LLM outputs may lead to downstream security exploits, including code execution that compromises systems and exposes data.\nLLM06: 2025 Excessive Agency - Granting LLMs unchecked autonomy to take action can lead to unintended consequences, jeopardizing reliability, privacy, and trust.\nLLM07: 2025 System Prompt Leakage - Exposing system prompts can reveal sensitive information, such as credentials or security controls, leading to potential attacks.\nLLM08: 2025 Vector and Embedding Weaknesses - Insecure handling of vectors and embeddings in Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) systems can lead to data poisoning, model manipulation, and unauthorized access.\nLLM09: 2025 Misinformation - LLMs can generate false or misleading information that appears credible, leading to security risks, reputational damage, and legal liability.\nLLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption - Allowing excessive and uncontrolled LLM inferences can lead to denial of service (DoS), financial loss, model theft, and service degradation.## MITRE ATLAS:\nAML.T0000: Search for Victim's Publicly Available Research Materials - Adversaries may search publicly available research to learn how and where machine learning is used within a victim organization.\nAML.T0001: Search for Publicly Available Adversarial Vulnerability Analysis - An adversary will likely try to identify any pre-existing researches available on the vulnerabilities that has been done for this class of models.\nAML.T0002: Acquire Public ML Artifacts - Adversaries may search public sources for machine learning artifacts, including software stacks, datasets, and model configurations.\nAML.T0003: Search Victim-Owned Websites - Adversaries may search victim-owned websites for technical details, organizational information, key employee data, and business operations to aid in targeting.\nAML.T0004: Search Application Repositories - Adversaries may search open application repositories, such as Google Play and the App Store, for targeting information.\nAML.T0005: Create Proxy ML Model - Adversaries may obtain proxy models to simulate full offline access to the victim's target model.\nAML.T0006: Active Scanning - Adversaries may probe or scan victim systems for targeting, involving direct interaction unlike other reconnaissance methods.\nAML.T0007: Discover ML Artifacts - Adversaries may search private sources for machine learning artifacts, such as software stacks and data repositories, to refine attacks and identify targets for exfiltration or disruption.\nAML.T0008: Acquire Infrastructure - Adversaries may acquire or rent various infrastructure, including servers, domains, and web services, to support their operations.\nAML.T0010: ML Supply Chain Compromise - Adversaries may gain initial access by compromising the ML supply chain, sometimes requiring secondary access to complete their attack.\nAML.T0011: User Execution - An adversary may rely upon specific actions by a user in order to gain execution.\nAML.T0012: Valid Accounts - Adversaries may obtain and abuse credentials of existing accounts as a means of gaining Initial Access.\nAML.T0013: Discover ML Model Ontology - Adversaries may discover the ontology of a machine learning model's output space, for example, the types of objects a model can detect.\nAML.T0014: Discover ML Model Family - Adversaries may discover the general family of model.\nAML.T0015: Evade ML Model - Adversaries can craft adversarial data that prevent a machine learning model from correctly identifying the contents of the data.\nAML.T0016: Obtain Capabilities - Adversaries may search for and obtain software capabilities for use in their operations.\nAML.T0017: Develop Capabilities - Adversaries may develop their own capabilities to support operations. This process encompasses identifying requirements, building solutions, and deploying capabilities.\nAML.T0018: Backdoor ML Model - Adversaries may implant backdoors in ML models, causing them to behave normally but produce adversary-controlled outputs when triggered.\nAML.T0019: Publish Poisoned Datasets - Adversaries may poison training data and publish it to a public location.\nAML.T0020: Poison Training Data - Adversaries may attempt to poison datasets used by a ML model by modifying the underlying data or its labels.\nAML.T0021: Establish Accounts - Adversaries may create accounts with various services for use in targeting, to gain access to resources needed in ML Attack Staging, or for victim impersonation.\nAML.T0024: Exfiltration via ML Inference API - Adversaries may exfiltrate private information via ML Model Inference API Access.\nAML.T0025: Exfiltration via Cyber Means - Adversaries may exfiltrate ML artifacts or other information relevant to their goals via traditional cyber means.\nAML.T0029: Denial of ML Service - Adversaries may target machine learning systems with a flood of requests for the purpose of degrading or shutting down the service.\nAML.T0031: Erode ML Model Integrity - Adversaries may degrade the target model's performance with adversarial data inputs to erode confidence in the system over time.\nAML.T0034: Cost Harvesting - Adversaries may target different machine learning services to send useless queries or computationally expensive inputs to increase the cost of running services at the victim organization.\nAML.T0035: ML Artifact Collection - Adversaries may collect ML artifacts, such as models, datasets, and telemetry data, for Exfiltration or for use in ML Attack Staging.\nAML.T0036: Data from Information Repositories - Adversaries may leverage information repositories to mine valuable information.\nAML.T0037: Data from Local System - Adversaries may search local system sources, such as file systems and configuration files or local databases, to find files of interest and sensitive data prior to Exfiltration.\nAML.T0040: ML Model Inference API Access - Adversaries may gain access to a model via legitimate access to the inference API to Discover ML Model Ontology, Model Family, to Verify Attack, Craft Adversarial Data, Evade ML Model, Erode ML Model Integrity.\nAML.T0041: Physical Environment Access - If the model is interacting with data collected from the real world in some way, the adversary can influence the model through access to wherever the data is being collected.\nAML.T0042: Verify Attack - Adversaries can verify the efficacy of their attack via an inference API or access to an offline copy of the target model.\nAML.T0043: Craft Adversarial Data - Adversarial data are inputs to a machine learning model that have been modified such that they cause the adversary's desired effect in the target model.\nAML.T0044: Full ML Model Access - Adversaries may gain full \"white-box\" access to a machine learning model, including its architecture, parameters, and class ontology.\nAML.T0046: Spamming ML System with Chaff Data - Adversaries may flood the ML system with chaff data, increasing detections and causing analysts to waste time on incorrect inferences.\nAML.T0047: ML-Enabled Product or Service - Adversaries may use a product or service that uses machine learning under the hood to gain access to the underlying machine learning model.\nAML.T0048: External Harms - Adversaries may abuse their access to a victim system and use its resources or capabilities to further their goals by causing harms external to that system.\nAML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application - Adversaries may exploit weaknesses in internet-facing systems, such as bugs or design flaws, to induce unintended behavior.\nAML.T0050: Command and Scripting Interpreter - Adversaries may abuse command and script interpreters to execute commands, scripts, or binaries.\nAML.T0051: LLM Prompt Injection - An adversary may craft malicious prompts as inputs to an LLM that cause the LLM to act in unintended ways.\nAML.T0052: Phishing - Adversaries may send phishing messages to gain access to victim systems.\nAML.T0053: LLM Plugin Compromise - Adversaries may use their access to an LLM that is part of a larger system to compromise connected plugins.\nAML.T0054: LLM Jailbreak - An adversary may use a carefully crafted LLM Prompt Injection designed to place LLM in a state in which it will freely respond to any user input, bypassing any controls, restrictions, or guardrails placed on the LLM.\nAML.T0055: Unsecured Credentials - Adversaries may search compromised systems to find and obtain insecurely stored credentials.\nAML.T0056: LLM Meta Prompt Extraction - An adversary may induce an LLM to reveal its initial instructions, or \"meta prompt\" and get sensitive information about the internal workings of the system.\nAML.T0057: LLM Data Leakage - Adversaries may craft prompts that induce the LLM to leak sensitive information. This can include private user data or proprietary information.\n\n\n\n# Reasoning Steps\nFirst, think carefully step by step about the user's system, elements, connections and applicable threats. Then, construct a report."
        },
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "Below is a complete, security-focused description of all notable elements and their connections found in the provided Terraform configuration. Each element is tagged with a STRIDE-per-element category in parentheses: External Entity, Process, Data Flow, Data Store. Trust boundaries are described separately (not classified).\n\nElements\n\n- Terraform Operator Workstation (External Entity)\n  - The host running terraform apply. Executes multiple local-exec provisioners (sed, Python scripts, venv, pip). Holds and processes secrets during provisioning.\n\n- Terraform CLI and Provisioners (Process)\n  - Executes sed replacements, Python cosmos operations, file zipping, and blob uploads. Touches sensitive values (Cosmos primary key, storage connection string, SAS).\n\n- Azure Resource Manager / Control Plane (Process)\n  - Target of Terraform API calls to create/update Azure resources.\n\n- Existing Azure Resource Group: var.resource_group = \"azuregoat_app\" (Trust container; described under trust boundaries)\n\n- azurerm_storage_account.storage_account (Data Store)\n  - Storage account: Standard/LRS, allow_nested_items_to_be_public = true, open public endpoints (no network rules specified).\n  - Blob CORS configured with:\n    - allowed_origins = [\"*\"], allowed_methods = [\"GET\",\"HEAD\",\"POST\",\"PUT\"], allowed_headers = [\"*\"], exposed_headers = [\"*\"], max_age = 3600.\n  - Security implications: Public blob access allowed at container/blob level; permissive CORS; no private endpoints; keys/connection strings used broadly.\n\n- azurerm_storage_container.storage_container (Data Store)\n  - Name: appazgoat{rand}-storage-container, access_type = \"blob\" (anonymous read of blobs, no listing).\n\n- azurerm_storage_container.storage_container_prod (Data Store)\n  - access_type = \"blob\" (anonymous read of blobs, no listing).\n\n- azurerm_storage_container.storage_container_dev (Data Store)\n  - access_type = \"container\" (anonymous read and listing).\n\n- azurerm_storage_container.storage_container_vm (Data Store)\n  - access_type = \"container\" (anonymous read and listing).\n\n- data.azurerm_storage_account_blob_container_sas.storage_account_blob_container_sas (Data Store)\n  - Container SAS token (secret) for storage_container; valid ~10 days; permissions: read, add, create, write; list = false; no IP or protocol restrictions specified.\n  - Embedded in function app app settings (exposed to application).\n\n- azurerm_storage_blob.storage_blob (Data Store)\n  - Blob: modules/module-1/resources/azure_function/data/data-api.zip (function package).\n  - Publicly accessible via URL plus SAS (embedded in function app settings).\n\n- azurerm_storage_blob.storage_blob_front (Data Store)\n  - Blob: modules/module-1/resources/azure_function/react/func.zip (frontend function package).\n\n- azurerm_storage_blob.app_files_prod (Data Store)\n  - Static site and related files uploaded to prod container (anonymous read of blobs).\n\n- azurerm_storage_blob.app_files_dev (Data Store)\n  - Static site and related files uploaded to dev container (anonymous read + listing).\n\n- azurerm_storage_blob.app_files_vm (Data Store)\n  - Static site and related files uploaded to vm container (anonymous read + listing).\n\n- azurerm_storage_blob.config_update_prod|dev|vm (Data Store)\n  - Uploads modules/.../.ssh/config.txt containing VM IP to each container. In dev and vm containers, listing + anonymous read exposes IP info; in prod, anonymous blob read exposes the file if path is known.\n\n- azurerm_cosmosdb_account.db (Data Store)\n  - SQL API (GlobalDocumentDB, serverless), single region (eastus).\n  - Consistency: BoundedStaleness (max_interval 300s, staleness_prefix 100,000).\n  - No firewall or private endpoint specified; key-based access used (primary_key in app settings).\n  - Secrets (endpoint, primary_key) substituted into code and function app settings.\n\n- null_resource.file_populate_data (Process)\n  - local-exec: sed substitution in JSON, sets up Python venv, installs azure-cosmos, runs create-table.py to initialize Cosmos DB.\n  - Depends on Cosmos DB and storage resources. Runs from operator workstation; uses credentials resolved from context/files.\n\n- null_resource.env_replace (Process)\n  - Injects Cosmos DB primary key and endpoint, storage connection string, and container name into modules/module-1/resources/azure_function/data/local.settings.json via sed.\n  - Risks putting secrets into packaged code.\n\n- data.archive_file.file_function_app (Process)\n  - Zips the backend function source directory (which includes local.settings.json after replacement).\n\n- azurerm_app_service_plan.app_service_plan (Process)\n  - Linux consumption plan for Functions (kind FunctionApp, sku Y1).\n\n- azurerm_function_app.function_app (Process)\n  - Backend API (Python 3.9, Linux). version \"~3\".\n  - App settings:\n    - WEBSITE_RUN_FROM_PACKAGE points to blob URL with container SAS (R/A/C/W perms).\n    - FUNCTIONS_WORKER_RUNTIME = python.\n    - JWT_SECRET hardcoded \"T2BYL6#]zc>Byuzu\".\n    - AZ_DB_ENDPOINT and AZ_DB_PRIMARYKEY (Cosmos secrets).\n    - CON_STR (storage primary connection string) and CONTAINER_NAME.\n  - site_config:\n    - linux_fx_version = python|3.9.\n    - cors allowed_origins [\"*\"].\n  - storage_account_name/access_key configured (host storage).\n  - https_only not set (HTTP likely allowed).\n  - No IP restrictions or private endpoints.\n\n- data.archive_file.file_function_app_front (Process)\n  - Zips the React-based function project for frontend.\n\n- azurerm_function_app.function_app_front (Process)\n  - Frontend function (Node.js 12, EOL). version \"~3\".\n  - App settings:\n    - WEBSITE_RUN_FROM_PACKAGE -> blob URL with container SAS (R/A/C/W).\n    - FUNCTIONS_WORKER_RUNTIME = node.\n    - AzureWebJobsDisableHomepage = true.\n  - site_config:\n    - linux_fx_version = node|12.\n  - https_only not set; no auth/CORS settings specified at app level (frontend behavior driven by code).\n\n- null_resource.file_replacement_upload (Process)\n  - Rewrites frontend HTML/JS to:\n    - Point asset URLs to prod storage container over HTTPS.\n    - Inject Azure Function backend hostname into frontend JS.\n  - Prepares static artifacts for upload.\n\n- null_resource.file_replacement_vm_ip (Process)\n  - Replaces VM_IP_ADDR placeholder in .ssh/config.txt with actual VM public IP.\n\n- azurerm_network_security_group.net_sg (Process)\n  - Inbound rule allows SSH (TCP/22) from any source to any destination (priority 1000). No deny rules restricting other traffic specified (defaults apply).\n\n- azurerm_virtual_network.vNet and azurerm_subnet.vNet_subnet (Trust boundary; see boundaries)\n\n- azurerm_public_ip.VM_PublicIP (Process)\n  - Public IP (Basic, Dynamic), DNS label: developervm-{rand}. Publicly reachable.\n\n- data.azurerm_public_ip.vm_ip (Process)\n  - Reads assigned VM public IP to inject into files.\n\n- azurerm_network_interface.net_int (Process)\n  - NIC with dynamic private IP and associated public IP; later attached to NSG.\n\n- azurerm_network_interface_security_group_association.example (Process)\n  - Binds NSG to NIC.\n\n- azurerm_virtual_machine.dev-vm (Process)\n  - Linux VM: UbuntuServer 18.04-LTS (EOL), Standard_B1s.\n  - delete_os_disk_on_termination = true.\n  - Identity: SystemAssigned (MSI).\n  - Admin auth:\n    - admin_username = azureuser.\n    - admin_password = \"St0r95p@$sw0rd@1265463541\" (hardcoded).\n    - disable_password_authentication = false (enables password login).\n  - Publicly reachable via SSH; no Just-In-Time or restricted source IPs defined.\n\n- azurerm_virtual_machine_extension.test (Process)\n  - CustomScript extension (Microsoft.Azure.Extensions, type CustomScript 2.0).\n  - Runs a base64-encoded script (config.sh templatefile). Receives URL param pointing to prod container webfiles path.\n\n- data.azurerm_subscription.primary, data.azurerm_client_config.example (Process)\n  - Read metadata for role scope and client context.\n\n- azurerm_user_assigned_identity.user_id (Data Store)\n  - User-assigned managed identity for automation. Holds credentials inside Azure (token issuance).\n\n- azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_vm (Process)\n  - Assigns Contributor role at resource-group scope to the VM\u2019s SystemAssigned identity (broad permissions over RG resources).\n\n- azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_identity (Process)\n  - Assigns Owner role at resource-group scope to the user-assigned identity (full control).\n\n- azurerm_automation_account.dev_automation_account_test (Process)\n  - Automation account (Basic). Uses user-assigned identity above.\n\n- null_resource.clientid_replacement (Process)\n  - Injects identity client_id and RG name into PowerShell runbook file (listVM.ps1) via sed.\n\n- data.local_file.runbook_file (Data Store)\n  - Contains the contents of the modified runbook script.\n\n- azurerm_automation_runbook.dev_automation_runbook (Process)\n  - Runbook: PowerShellWorkflow \"Get-AzureVM\"; log_verbose/progress enabled. Capable of interacting with Azure using the attached identity (Owner at RG).\n\n- random_id.randomId (Process)\n  - Generates random suffixes for resource names (not security-relevant by itself).\n\n- Locals (Process)\n  - now/sasExpiry/date formatting used to establish SAS start/expiry windows.\n\nData Flows\n\n- Terraform CLI -> Azure Resource Manager (Data Flow)\n  - Creates and configures all resources using provider credentials. Scope: subscription/resource group.\n\n- Terraform Operator Workstation -> Local files (Data Flow)\n  - sed replacements inject secrets into local.settings.json and PS1; zips content; writes .ssh/config.txt with VM IP.\n\n- Terraform Operator Workstation -> Cosmos DB (Data Flow)\n  - create-table.py executed locally uses Azure Cosmos SDK to create/seed data (uses Cosmos endpoint/key from files or environment).\n\n- Terraform Operator Workstation -> Storage Account (Data Flow)\n  - Uploads zipped function packages and static assets via Azure APIs using account key/connection string from provider context.\n\n- End User Browser -> azurerm_function_app.function_app_front (Data Flow)\n  - HTTP/HTTPS requests to frontend function app; https_only is not enforced, so HTTP is likely allowed.\n\n- azurerm_function_app.function_app_front -> Storage Account (Data Flow)\n  - WEBSITE_RUN_FROM_PACKAGE causes Azure to fetch func.zip from blob using SAS (GET with SAS; R/A/C/W on container SAS though only read needed).\n\n- End User Browser -> Storage Account containers (Data Flow)\n  - Anonymous GETs of static web files:\n    - prod: anonymous read of blobs (non-listable).\n    - dev/vm: anonymous read + listing (container-level public).\n  - CORS on blob service allows requests from any origin and methods including PUT/POST (authentication still required for writes).\n\n- Frontend JS (Browser) -> azurerm_function_app.function_app (Data Flow)\n  - API calls from frontend to backend function app (hostname injected into JS). CORS on backend allows [\"*\"].\n\n- azurerm_function_app.function_app -> Cosmos DB (Data Flow)\n  - Uses AZ_DB_ENDPOINT and AZ_DB_PRIMARYKEY to perform CRUD operations.\n\n- azurerm_function_app.function_app -> Storage Account (Data Flow)\n  - Uses storage primary connection string (account key) and container name for blob operations (full account-level privileges).\n\n- VM CustomScript Extension -> Storage Account (Data Flow)\n  - config.sh executes and may fetch additional resources/content using provided URL pointing to prod container webfiles.\n\n- Azure Automation Runbook -> Azure Resource Manager (Data Flow)\n  - Runbook authenticates with user-assigned identity (Owner) and can enumerate/control resources (e.g., VMs) within the RG.\n\n- Terraform data source -> Public IP service (Data Flow)\n  - Reads the VM public IP and injects into .ssh/config.txt; then publishes to public storage blobs.\n\nTrust Boundaries\n\n- Internet to Azure App Services boundary\n  - Both function apps expose public endpoints under azurewebsites.net.\n  - https_only not enforced; CORS on backend allows any origin.\n  - Node 12 frontend runtime is EOL, increasing exposure risk.\n\n- Internet to Azure Storage (Blob) boundary\n  - Storage account publicly accessible. Multiple containers configured for anonymous access:\n    - prod: blob-level public (no listing).\n    - dev/vm: container-level public (listing + blob read).\n  - Very permissive blob CORS (* origins, wide methods/headers).\n  - Public exposure of files including .ssh/config.txt with VM IP.\n\n- Azure Control Plane boundary\n  - Terraform and Automation interact with ARM. Two identities with broad privileges:\n    - VM SystemAssigned identity: Contributor on RG.\n    - Automation UserAssigned identity: Owner on RG.\n\n- Azure PaaS to PaaS boundary (Function App <-> Cosmos DB, Storage)\n  - All via public endpoints; no Private Endpoints or VNet integration defined.\n\n- Deployment Host to Cloud boundary\n  - Secrets are processed on the operator workstation and written into local files and packages prior to upload.\n\n- VM Public Exposure boundary\n  - NSG allows SSH from any source; Basic Public IP; password-based auth enabled; OS image Ubuntu 18.04-LTS (EOL).\n\nKey Security Observations (prioritized)\n\n- Public endpoints and CORS\n  - Function app backend has CORS allowed_origins [\"*\"].\n  - Storage blob CORS allows \"*\" origins and methods including PUT/POST; combined with public containers, this expands attack surface (though write still needs auth).\n  - Function apps do not enforce https_only; HTTP access likely enabled.\n\n- Secret handling\n  - Cosmos DB primary key, storage account primary connection string, and JWT_SECRET are stored in app settings and injected into local.settings.json that is zipped into packages.\n  - WEBSITE_RUN_FROM_PACKAGE uses a container SAS with read/add/create/write for 10 days; over-privileged for read-only code fetch; SAS embedded in app settings.\n  - Prefer Azure Key Vault references and Managed Identity over keys/connection strings.\n\n- Storage account/public access\n  - allow_nested_items_to_be_public = true. Multiple containers are public; dev/vm containers are listable.\n  - Uploads .ssh/config.txt with live VM IP to public containers (information disclosure).\n\n- VM exposure\n  - SSH open to 0.0.0.0/0 (NSG).\n  - Password-based SSH enabled with a hardcoded password.\n  - OS image Ubuntu 18.04-LTS (EOL).\n  - VM\u2019s managed identity has Contributor on RG (risk of lateral movement/escalation if VM compromised).\n\n- Privilege model\n  - User-assigned identity has Owner at RG scope and is attached to Automation Account; compromise of runbook/automation could lead to full RG takeover.\n\n- Network isolation\n  - No Private Endpoints or service endpoints for Storage or Cosmos DB.\n  - No VNet integration for Function Apps; all data over public endpoints.\n\n- Runtime versions\n  - Frontend Function App uses node|12 (EOL). Backend Python 3.9 still supported as of 2025 but nearing end of standard support; keep patched.\n\n- Misc\n  - Basic SKU Public IP (no advanced features), idle timeout 4 minutes.\n  - No diagnostic settings/logging/alerts configured; no WAF/App Gateway in front of apps.\n\nSuggested Hardenings (high-level)\n\n- Enforce https_only on both function apps; restrict CORS to known origins and necessary methods/headers.\n- Remove public access from storage containers (set private) and disable allow_nested_items_to_be_public unless required. If public hosting is needed, use a CDN/front door with WAF and signed URLs.\n- Use Managed Identity and Key Vault references; replace Cosmos keys and storage connection strings with MI-based RBAC; limit SAS to read-only and shortest lifetime.\n- Lock down SSH: restrict NSG source IPs, disable password auth (use SSH keys), upgrade OS to supported LTS, consider JIT access via Defender for Cloud.\n- Reduce RBAC scope: limit VM MSI to least privilege; remove Owner from automation identity unless absolutely required.\n- Add Private Endpoints for Cosmos DB and Storage; enable Function App VNet integration.\n- Update frontend runtime to supported Node LTS.\n- Avoid embedding secrets in packages (do not include local.settings.json in deployable artifacts).\n- Add monitoring/diagnostics: App Service logs, Storage/Cosmos diagnostics, alerting, and deny public storage where possible via Azure Policies.\n\nThis description enumerates all elements, their configurations, and the critical security-relevant connections to support subsequent threat modeling."
        },
        {
            "role": "assistant",
            "content": "{\"message\":\"Approach: STRIDE-per-Element with trust boundaries and data flows considered. For each element, threats are enumerated per the matrix (External Entity: Spoofing/Repudiation; Process: all STRIDE; Data Store: Tampering/Repudiation/Info Disclosure/DoS; Data Flow: Tampering/Info Disclosure/DoS). OWASP LLM Top 10 and MITRE ATLAS ML techniques are not applicable here because no LLM/ML components exist; those fields are set to null. Priority is given to high-risk misconfigurations observed (public storage/CORS, weak secrets handling, SAS over-privilege, VM exposure, broad RBAC, plaintext/HTTP). This is part 1 of the report; additional elements and flows will follow if needed.\",\"threats\":[{\"id\":1,\"element\":\"Terraform Operator Workstation\",\"threat_description\":\"An attacker could spoof the operator workstation identity or tooling to run terraform apply with the same credentials, pushing malicious changes.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use strong MFA for provider auth, hardware-backed credentials, restrict where applies can run, IP allow-list, and sign Terraform plans/state changes (remote backend with RBAC).\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":2,\"element\":\"Terraform Operator Workstation\",\"threat_description\":\"Operator could repudiate destructive actions (no traceability for local-exec and manual secret handling).\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use remote state with audit logs, enable Azure Activity Logs/Defender, log local-exec output to append-only storage, code review and signed commits, require change approvals.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":3,\"element\":\"Terraform CLI and Provisioners\",\"threat_description\":\"Malicious inputs or environment spoofing could cause Terraform/provisioners to execute under attacker-provided credentials or endpoints.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Pin providers with checksums, lock provider versions, validate backend/tenant IDs, use explicit subscription/tenant in providers, and scoped service principals with least privilege.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":4,\"element\":\"Terraform CLI and Provisioners\",\"threat_description\":\"sed/Python steps can be tampered to inject backdoors or alter code packages before upload.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use immutable build pipeline, signed artifacts, verify hashes before upload, ensure local scripts are from version-controlled sources, enable Defender for DevOps controls.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":5,\"element\":\"Terraform CLI and Provisioners\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of auditing for local-exec steps enables denial or dispute of secret use and file modifications.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Redirect stdout/stderr to append-only logs, store in secure logging service, maintain change management with approvals and signed plan/apply.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":6,\"element\":\"Terraform CLI and Provisioners\",\"threat_description\":\"Secrets (Cosmos key, storage connection string, SAS, JWT) handled in plaintext files risk leakage to disk, archives, or logs.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use Key Vault references and Managed Identity, avoid writing secrets to local.settings.json, scrub logs, use environment variables or ephemeral secret mounts, and encrypt local disks.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":7,\"element\":\"Terraform CLI and Provisioners\",\"threat_description\":\"Long-running or recursive local tasks can hang pipeline or exhaust local resources, delaying or blocking deployment.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Set explicit timeouts, resource limits, and retries; isolate heavy tasks into CI runners; use remote build stages.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":8,\"element\":\"Terraform CLI and Provisioners\",\"threat_description\":\"Executing arbitrary scripts with provider credentials can lead to privilege escalation across Azure resources.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Run with least-privileged service principal, split applies by scope, enforce policy as code (Azure Policy/OPA), and restrict local-exec to whitelisted scripts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":9,\"element\":\"Azure Resource Manager / Control Plane\",\"threat_description\":\"Attackers may impersonate valid accounts or tokens to ARM to create/alter resources.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Conditional Access + MFA, workload identities with minimal scopes, verify tenant/subscription IDs, use management group policies to deny risky actions, monitor sign-ins.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":10,\"element\":\"Azure Resource Manager / Control Plane\",\"threat_description\":\"Unauthorized template or API changes can tamper resource configurations (e.g., open storage, broad roles).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Azure Policy/Deny assignments, Blueprints, role separation, Defender for Cloud alerts on configuration drift, approval gates.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":11,\"element\":\"Azure Resource Manager / Control Plane\",\"threat_description\":\"If Activity Logs/diagnostics are not enabled/retained, resource changes can be denied or unattributed.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable Azure Activity Logs with long-term retention, Log Analytics, immutable storage for logs, and alerts for high-impact operations.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":12,\"element\":\"Azure Resource Manager / Control Plane\",\"threat_description\":\"Overly permissive outputs or misconfigured diagnostics could expose secrets/endpoints.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Mask sensitive outputs, limit who can read deployment outputs/state, enable Key Vault purge protection and secret scoping.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":13,\"element\":\"Azure Resource Manager / Control Plane\",\"threat_description\":\"Automated or malicious scripts can flood ARM with create/update calls causing throttling and deployment failure.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Rate-limit CI/CD, stagger deployments, monitor ARM throttling metrics, implement backoffs/retries.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":14,\"element\":\"Azure Resource Manager / Control Plane\",\"threat_description\":\"Excessive privileges at RG scope (Owner/Contributor) enable elevation across services and lateral movement.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Apply least privilege (custom roles), remove Owner from automation identity, use PIM for just-in-time elevation with approval and logging.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":15,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_account.storage_account\",\"threat_description\":\"Attackers with leaked keys/connection string/SAS can modify or upload blobs (code/packages).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Disable account key access (use Azure AD RBAC), rotate keys, scope SAS to read-only and shortest TTL, enable versioning/immutability and soft delete.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":16,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_account.storage_account\",\"threat_description\":\"Insufficient logging leads to inability to attribute blob/container changes made via SAS tokens.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable Storage Analytics/Diagnostic logs to Log Analytics, include SAS identifier (signedIdentifier), and retain logs with immutability.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":17,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_account.storage_account\",\"threat_description\":\"Public endpoints with permissive CORS and anonymous containers expose data and metadata.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Disable public access, restrict CORS to known origins/methods, use Private Endpoints and firewall, and serve public content via CDN/Front Door with WAF.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":18,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_account.storage_account\",\"threat_description\":\"Unbounded anonymous reads and expensive operations (e.g., range requests) can incur cost spikes or throttle the service.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use CDN caching, rate limiting at edge, private access, set Azure Monitor alerts on egress/transactions, and automatic scaling policies.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":19,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_container.storage_container (blob-level public)\",\"threat_description\":\"SAS token with write permissions allows code/package tampering within the container.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Issue read-only SAS for run-from-package, rotate SAS frequently, enable blob versioning/legal hold to prevent malicious overwrites.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":20,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_container.storage_container (blob-level public)\",\"threat_description\":\"Operations via SAS lack strong attribution if identifiers are not used.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use stored access policies with signedIdentifier, log to immutable storage, and correlate access logs with deployment pipeline IDs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":21,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_container.storage_container (blob-level public)\",\"threat_description\":\"Anonymous blob reads expose any blob whose path is known (e.g., code packages).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Set container access to private, restrict access via signed short-lived URLs through CDN, and avoid storing secrets or sensitive files.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":22,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_container.storage_container (blob-level public)\",\"threat_description\":\"High-rate anonymous reads can increase costs or degrade performance.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use CDN/front door caching with WAF rate limiting; monitor and alert on transaction spikes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":23,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_container.storage_container_prod (blob-level public)\",\"threat_description\":\"Known-path files (e.g., static assets) can be enumerated via references, risking leakage of embedded data.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Make container private, serve via CDN with signed URLs, and avoid sensitive content in public storage.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":24,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_container.storage_container_prod (blob-level public)\",\"threat_description\":\"If any write-capable SAS/keys leak, attackers could tamper production web files.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Eliminate account keys, use Azure AD RBAC, set immutability policies for prod containers, rotate credentials, CI-only writes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":25,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_container.storage_container_dev (container-level public)\",\"threat_description\":\"Anonymous listing exposes file names, paths, and configuration artifacts useful for reconnaissance.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Switch to private access; if public is required, disable listing (blob-level at most) and scrub sensitive files.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":26,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_container.storage_container_dev (container-level public)\",\"threat_description\":\"Publicly listable container enables targeted tampering if write credentials are later compromised.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use RBAC, no shared keys; enable versioning and change feed to detect and revert malicious edits.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":27,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_container.storage_container_vm (container-level public)\",\"threat_description\":\"Anonymous listing and reads of VM-related artifacts (.ssh/config.txt) disclose VM IP and structure.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Remove public access; do not publish internal config; store such files in private storage or Key Vault secrets.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":28,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_container.storage_container_vm (container-level public)\",\"threat_description\":\"If write creds leak, attacker can replace VM bootstrap artifacts fetched by users/scripts.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Private container with SAS scoped to read-only; pin bootstraps by hash; enable immutability.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":29,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_storage_account_blob_container_sas.storage_account_blob_container_sas\",\"threat_description\":\"Over-privileged SAS (R/A/C/W) and long TTL can be abused to upload/modify blobs.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Issue read-only SAS, shortest possible TTL, IP/protocol restrictions; prefer user delegation SAS via Azure AD and Managed Identity.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":30,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_storage_account_blob_container_sas.storage_account_blob_container_sas\",\"threat_description\":\"SAS token in app settings or code can leak, with limited forensic attribution.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Store in Key Vault references; do not bundle in packages; use App Service slot settings; minimize exposure in logs; rotate frequently.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":31,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_storage_account_blob_container_sas.storage_account_blob_container_sas\",\"threat_description\":\"SAS usage without stored access policies limits ability to revoke and attribute actions (repudiation risk).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Tie SAS to stored access policies; log access; bind to IPs; keep identifiers to correlate with pipelines.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":32,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_storage_account_blob_container_sas.storage_account_blob_container_sas\",\"threat_description\":\"Abuse of write permissions can cause cost spikes or saturation (many small writes/creates).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Scope SAS to minimal perms, monitor transaction metrics, alerts on anomalies, and auto-rotate on spikes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":33,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.storage_blob (backend package)\",\"threat_description\":\"Package blob can be replaced if write-capable SAS/keys are compromised, injecting malicious backend code.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Read-only SAS for run-from-package, sign packages and verify signature at startup, enable blob immutability/versioning.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":34,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.storage_blob (backend package)\",\"threat_description\":\"Blob URL and SAS embedded in app settings risk disclosure and unauthorized download.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Do not expose SAS in settings; prefer MSI + user delegation SAS generated at runtime; restrict referer/IP; short TTL.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":35,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.storage_blob (backend package)\",\"threat_description\":\"High-rate downloads of package blob can cause egress/cost DoS.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Cache via CDN, restrict access, monitor egress, rotate URLs frequently.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":36,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.storage_blob_front (frontend package)\",\"threat_description\":\"Frontend package blob could be tampered to serve malicious JS if write creds leak.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Sign and integrity-check assets (SRI), read-only SAS, versioning and legal hold for release artifacts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":37,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.app_files_dev\",\"threat_description\":\"Public listing and reads disclose application structure and potential secrets committed by mistake.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Make dev container private; run content scanners to prevent secret commits; separate dev from internet-facing endpoints.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":38,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.app_files_vm\",\"threat_description\":\"VM container file listing reveals infrastructure details (e.g., paths, config), aiding attackers.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Set container to private; do not publish infrastructure configs; move to private storage.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":39,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.config_update_dev|vm\",\"threat_description\":\"Public .ssh/config.txt exposes live VM IP, enabling targeted probing and brute force.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Do not publish; remove file or store privately; rotate VM IPs; restrict SSH sources; disable password auth.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":40,\"element\":\"azurerm_cosmosdb_account.db\",\"threat_description\":\"Primary key in app settings enables full data tampering if application is compromised.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use Azure AD RBAC with Managed Identity; remove key auth; rotate keys; apply strict roles (read, limited write); enable resource tokens for granular access.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":41,\"element\":\"azurerm_cosmosdb_account.db\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of detailed audit on operations using keys/SAS hinders attribution (repudiation).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable Cosmos diagnostic logs to Log Analytics/Event Hub, correlate with app identity; disable key auth to improve attribution via AAD.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":42,\"element\":\"azurerm_cosmosdb_account.db\",\"threat_description\":\"Public endpoint plus key exposure risks data exfiltration (bounded staleness still leaks).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Private Endpoint, firewall trusted sources, remove key auth, store secrets in Key Vault, TLS enforcement, client-side field encryption where feasible.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":43,\"element\":\"azurerm_cosmosdb_account.db\",\"threat_description\":\"Query floods or RU-expensive operations can degrade availability or increase costs (serverless).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Rate limit at app/API gateway, set alerts on RU usage and throttling, use autoscale limits, create fail-open/queue patterns.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":44,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_populate_data\",\"threat_description\":\"Using local Cosmos credentials could be spoofed via env/file manipulation to point at attacker Cosmos endpoint.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Pin endpoints by hostname/tenant, validate TLS certs, store endpoints securely, use MSI where possible.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":45,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_populate_data\",\"threat_description\":\"Script can be tampered to seed backdoored data or create over-privileged containers.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Code review, signed scripts, hash verification, limit script permissions; run from trusted build agents.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":46,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_populate_data\",\"threat_description\":\"No persistent audit of seed operations impairs traceability.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Log operations to central SIEM, include correlation IDs, and retain script outputs immutably.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":47,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_populate_data\",\"threat_description\":\"Secrets for Cosmos are handled locally risking disclosure via files or process list.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use MSI + AAD RBAC, avoid plaintext files, mask environment variables, scrub shell history.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":48,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_populate_data\",\"threat_description\":\"Script loops or large imports can lock resources and stall deployments.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Define timeouts and batch limits; pre-validate data; run offline initialization where possible.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":49,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_populate_data\",\"threat_description\":\"Script\u2019s access to primary keys enables broader-than-needed operations (EoP if compromised).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use scoped roles and MSI; avoid primary keys; apply least-privileged accounts for seeding only.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":50,\"element\":\"null_resource.env_replace\",\"threat_description\":\"Environment replacement can be spoofed to inject attacker-controlled endpoints/keys into app config.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Template signing, verify values against Key Vault, restrict write access to config files, CI-controlled substitutions only.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":51,\"element\":\"null_resource.env_replace\",\"threat_description\":\"sed replacements can corrupt config or insert backdoors (tampering).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use structured config tools (jq/yq), schema validation, and integrity checking post-substitution.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":52,\"element\":\"null_resource.env_replace\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of audit for local config edits hampers attribution.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Commit changes to VCS or record diffs to immutable logs; code review required for config changes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":53,\"element\":\"null_resource.env_replace\",\"threat_description\":\"Secrets written into local.settings.json risk leakage into packages and repos.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Exclude local.settings.json from package; use Key Vault references; keep secrets in app settings (slot) only; scan artifacts for secrets.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":54,\"element\":\"null_resource.env_replace\",\"threat_description\":\"Broken config can crash the app or block deployment.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use config validation and health checks; safe deploy with slots; rollbacks.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":55,\"element\":\"null_resource.env_replace\",\"threat_description\":\"Injecting broader privileges (e.g., storage account key) increases blast radius if app compromised.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Replace connection strings with scoped MSI-based RBAC; drop account keys; apply least privilege per operation.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":56,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app (backend)\",\"threat_description\":\"No auth and CORS [\\\"*\\\"] allow spoofed clients to call APIs as trusted origins.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enforce auth (AAD/JWT validation), restrict CORS to known origins, require HTTPS and tokens, implement API gateway/WAF.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":57,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app (backend)\",\"threat_description\":\"WEBSITE_RUN_FROM_PACKAGE via write-capable SAS permits package tampering if leaked.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use read-only SAS; verify package signatures; store package in private storage with MSI; enable SCM build with signed artifacts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":58,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app (backend)\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of diagnostic logging can hinder attribution of API actions or config changes.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable App Service logs, audit, and Azure Monitor; keep logs in immutable storage and correlate with client identities.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":59,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app (backend)\",\"threat_description\":\"HTTP not forced (https_only false) risks sniffing tokens/secrets in transit; app settings include sensitive keys.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Set https_only true; enable HSTS; move secrets to Key Vault references; restrict app settings access; rotate secrets.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":60,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app (backend)\",\"threat_description\":\"Unbounded requests can exhaust function concurrency or budgets (cold start thrash).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use WAF/rate limiting, quotas, caching, and queue-based triggers; scale out limits and alerts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":61,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app (backend)\",\"threat_description\":\"Compromise of function leads to access with storage account key and Cosmos primary key (broad EoP).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Remove connection strings/keys; use MSI + RBAC with least privilege; segment data access; secrets via Key Vault references; rotate keys.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:H/SA:M\"},{\"id\":62,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app_front (frontend)\",\"threat_description\":\"EOL Node 12 runtime increases spoofing via known vulnerabilities and supply-chain risks.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Upgrade to supported LTS; pin dependencies; SCA scanning; enforce HTTPS and auth as required.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":63,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app_front (frontend)\",\"threat_description\":\"Package blob for frontend can be tampered leading to malicious client-side code delivery.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Read-only SAS, SRI for scripts, content signing, immutable releases.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":64,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app_front (frontend)\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of https_only exposes clients to MITM and data leakage.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable https_only and HSTS; front with WAF/CDN; disable HTTP bindings.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":65,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app_front (frontend)\",\"threat_description\":\"Flooding requests or expensive functions can lead to service saturation.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Rate limit at edge, cache static responses, protect endpoints via WAF challenges/bot protection.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":66,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app_front (frontend)\",\"threat_description\":\"If compromised, frontend function could abuse managed credentials or environment to pivot (EoP).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Run with minimal app settings, disable unnecessary permissions, no account keys, use MSI with reader-only where possible.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":67,\"element\":\"azurerm_virtual_machine.dev-vm\",\"threat_description\":\"Password-based SSH with a hardcoded password allows spoofed logins via brute force/credential stuffing.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Disable password auth; use SSH keys; rotate admin; enforce allow-listed source IPs; enable JIT via Defender for Cloud.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":68,\"element\":\"azurerm_virtual_machine.dev-vm\",\"threat_description\":\"CustomScript or user actions can be tampered to run malicious code, especially if scripts fetched from modifiable storage.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Fetch scripts from private, immutable storage; verify hashes; use signed packages; restrict outbound and IMDS access as appropriate.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":69,\"element\":\"azurerm_virtual_machine.dev-vm\",\"threat_description\":\"Limited OS/audit logs or off-box forwarding can allow repudiation of attacker activity.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable Azure Monitor/AMA agent, syslog forwarding, tamper-evident logging, and Defender for Servers.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":70,\"element\":\"azurerm_virtual_machine.dev-vm\",\"threat_description\":\"EOL Ubuntu 18.04 and public IP expose vulnerabilities leading to data exfiltration (keys, tokens).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Upgrade to supported LTS; timely patching; restrict inbound; disable password auth; no sensitive data on VM; disk encryption.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":71,\"element\":\"azurerm_virtual_machine.dev-vm\",\"threat_description\":\"SSH open to 0.0.0.0/0 exposes service to brute force and resource exhaustion; small SKU can be overwhelmed.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Restrict NSG to trusted IPs, enable JIT, use fail2ban/SSH rate limiting, DDoS Protection plan.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":72,\"element\":\"azurerm_virtual_machine.dev-vm\",\"threat_description\":\"VM MSI has Contributor at RG; compromise allows elevation and control of RG resources via IMDS token.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Reduce MSI scope to least privilege; block IMDS from untrusted processes via egress ACLs; monitor MSI token usage; consider workload identity federation.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:H/SA:M\"},{\"id\":73,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_security_group.net_sg\",\"threat_description\":\"Open SSH rule from any source enables IP spoofed access attempts and broad exposure.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Narrow source prefixes, add Geo/IP reputation filtering via Azure Firewall/WAF, enable JIT.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":74,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_security_group.net_sg\",\"threat_description\":\"Rules can be tampered to open additional ports if credentials are compromised.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Lock down changes with Azure Policy (deny broad rules), RBAC separation, alerts on NSG changes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":75,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_security_group.net_sg\",\"threat_description\":\"If diagnostics are off, changes to NSG rules may be repudiated.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable NSG flow logs and activity logs to LA/Storage with immutability and alerts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":76,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_security_group.net_sg\",\"threat_description\":\"Overly permissive rules disclose internal services to the internet if added inadvertently.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Deny by default, restrict inbound, use service tags, regularly audit effective rules.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":77,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_security_group.net_sg\",\"threat_description\":\"Misconfigurations can allow high-volume traffic causing VM exhaustion or bandwidth costs.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Limit exposure, apply DDoS Protection Standard, rate-limit upstream, throttle SSH attempts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":78,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_security_group.net_sg\",\"threat_description\":\"If NSG is modified to allow management plane access or unusual egress, attacker gains broader privileges.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Restrict who can change NSGs; policy deny rules; continuous compliance scans; approvals for security rule changes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":79,\"element\":\"azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_identity (Owner at RG)\",\"threat_description\":\"Attacker can impersonate/abuse the Automation identity if credentials are exposed via runbook or system to perform owner-level actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use PIM for Owner with approvals and time limits; scope to minimal required roles; monitor sign-ins and token use.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:H/SA:M\"},{\"id\":80,\"element\":\"azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_identity (Owner at RG)\",\"threat_description\":\"Role assignment can be tampered to escalate privileges or widen scope.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Management group Azure Policies to restrict high-privilege role assignments; alerts on role changes; access reviews.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:N/SC:C/SI:H/SA:N\"},{\"id\":81,\"element\":\"azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_identity (Owner at RG)\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of strict logging or access reviews could allow repudiation of owner actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable Privileged Identity Management, log role activation, enforce approvals and justifications, immutable logging.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":82,\"element\":\"azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_identity (Owner at RG)\",\"threat_description\":\"Excessive privileges risk exposing secrets/resources across RG via misused runbooks or automation.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Reduce to least privilege; split roles by function; deny data-plane read of secrets where not needed; use KV firewalls and private endpoints.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":83,\"element\":\"azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_identity (Owner at RG)\",\"threat_description\":\"Owner role enables destructive actions leading to environment-wide outages.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Guardrails via Azure Policy locks, blueprints, and PIM; approval workflows for destructive operations; backups and soft delete.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":84,\"element\":\"azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_identity (Owner at RG)\",\"threat_description\":\"Owner provides full elevation path from any compromised automation surface to total RG control.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Remove Owner; use narrowly scoped custom roles; enforce PIM with short activations; break-glass accounts stored in vault with monitoring.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:C/SI:H/SA:H\"},{\"id\":85,\"element\":\"azurerm_automation_account.dev_automation_account_test\",\"threat_description\":\"RunAs identity or UAMI could be spoofed by executing runbooks that impersonate expected operations.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Require signed runbooks, approval before publish, RBAC separation for runbook Authors vs Operators, and output verification.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":86,\"element\":\"azurerm_automation_account.dev_automation_account_test\",\"threat_description\":\"Runbooks can be tampered to perform unintended actions under Owner privileges.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Version control, code signing, approvals; restrict who can edit/publish; peer review; scan scripts for dangerous cmdlets.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:H/SA:M\"},{\"id\":87,\"element\":\"azurerm_automation_account.dev_automation_account_test\",\"threat_description\":\"If logging is insufficient, malicious operator can repudiate actions taken via runbooks.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable job logs/streams to Log Analytics, immutable retention, and include change approval metadata within jobs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":88,\"element\":\"azurerm_automation_account.dev_automation_account_test\",\"threat_description\":\"Runbooks may output or handle secrets inadvertently leaking to logs.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use secure assets/variables, mask secrets in logs, Key Vault references, ensure runbooks avoid Write-Output of sensitive values.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":89,\"element\":\"azurerm_automation_account.dev_automation_account_test\",\"threat_description\":\"Misconfigured schedules or malicious loops can consume resources and starve other operations.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Quota policies, concurrency limits, timeouts on runbooks, and job throttling; alerts on long-running jobs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":90,\"element\":\"azurerm_automation_account.dev_automation_account_test\",\"threat_description\":\"Owner-level UAMI attached lets runbooks escalate to full RG control on compromise.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Replace Owner with custom least-privilege roles; PIM activation; segment runbooks by role scope.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:C/SI:H/SA:H\"},{\"id\":91,\"element\":\"End User Browser -> azurerm_function_app.function_app_front\",\"threat_description\":\"HTTP allowed enables in-transit tampering/MITM of requests and responses.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Force HTTPS, HSTS, redirect HTTP to HTTPS, TLS 1.2+, secure cookies and CSP.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":92,\"element\":\"End User Browser -> azurerm_function_app.function_app_front\",\"threat_description\":\"Sensitive data in transit could be sniffed over HTTP.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable https_only and HSTS; avoid sensitive data in GET params; use TLS pinning where applicable.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":93,\"element\":\"End User Browser -> azurerm_function_app.function_app_front\",\"threat_description\":\"Flood of requests from bots can degrade service and trigger cold starts.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"WAF with rate limiting/bot mitigation, CDN caching, request throttling, and auto-scale protections.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":94,\"element\":\"Frontend JS (Browser) -> azurerm_function_app.function_app (backend)\",\"threat_description\":\"With CORS [\\\"*\\\"] and no auth, attacker can tamper client requests (origin spoof) to invoke backend APIs.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Restrict CORS, enforce authentication/authorization at API, validate tokens server-side.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":95,\"element\":\"Frontend JS (Browser) -> azurerm_function_app.function_app (backend)\",\"threat_description\":\"Responses may include sensitive data that can be read by any origin due to permissive CORS.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Return minimal data, implement CORS allow-list, use tokens with least scopes, avoid reflecting secrets.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":96,\"element\":\"Frontend JS (Browser) -> azurerm_function_app.function_app (backend)\",\"threat_description\":\"Unbounded API calls can overwhelm function concurrency/compute allocations.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Rate limit per client/IP, use API Management, circuit breakers and queuing.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":97,\"element\":\"End User Browser -> Storage Account containers\",\"threat_description\":\"Anonymous requests allow tampering attempts when write-capable SAS is leaked via referrer or logs.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Ensure no write-capable SAS in public contexts, use read-only, short TTL, referer/IP restrictions, and CDN to hide origin.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":98,\"element\":\"End User Browser -> Storage Account containers\",\"threat_description\":\"Public listing/reads disclose file names and contents (dev/vm).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Set containers private or blob-level; minimize exposed data; avoid publishing config or IP data.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":99,\"element\":\"End User Browser -> Storage Account containers\",\"threat_description\":\"High-volume anonymous blob reads can throttle service or incur costs (egress DoS).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Front with CDN/WAF and rate limits; monitor; set budgets/alerts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":100,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app -> Cosmos DB\",\"threat_description\":\"Backend code injection or SSRF could tamper data using primary key.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use MSI + AAD RBAC with minimal permissions; validate inputs; segregate read/write operations; rotate keys and remove them from app.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":101,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app -> Cosmos DB\",\"threat_description\":\"Responses from Cosmos may include sensitive records; with public endpoints, leakage possible if app compromised.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Encrypt sensitive fields client-side; implement authorization checks; private endpoints; minimize returned data.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":102,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app -> Cosmos DB\",\"threat_description\":\"Hot loops or heavy queries can exhaust RU/s and cause throttling/outage.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Rate limit and cache; proper indexing; autoscale; backoff/retry with jitter; queue writes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":103,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app -> Storage Account (using account key)\",\"threat_description\":\"With full account key, backend can modify or delete any blob in the account if compromised.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Remove account key usage; use MSI with scoped RBAC; per-container permissions; data protection features (versioning/immutability).\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:N/SC:C/SI:H/SA:N\"},{\"id\":104,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app -> Storage Account (using account key)\",\"threat_description\":\"Storage connection string in app settings may leak via logs or vulnerabilities.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Key Vault references; no connection strings; rotate keys; restrict who can read app settings; private endpoints.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":105,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app -> Storage Account (using account key)\",\"threat_description\":\"Aggressive blob operations can saturate storage leading to throttling/cost DoS.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Rate limit writes, apply backpressure, alerts on transaction spikes, use queues for buffering.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":106,\"element\":\"VM CustomScript Extension -> Storage Account\",\"threat_description\":\"If script URL points to publicly modifiable content, fetched script can be tampered with.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Serve scripts from private containers with read-only SAS; verify hashes; pin exact blob version IDs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":107,\"element\":\"VM CustomScript Extension -> Storage Account\",\"threat_description\":\"Script content or tokens in URLs may be exposed in logs or telemetry.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Mask parameters in ARM; avoid embedding secrets in URLs; use MSI to fetch artifacts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":108,\"element\":\"VM CustomScript Extension -> Storage Account\",\"threat_description\":\"Large script downloads or repeated retries can cause throttling or delay VM provisioning.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Cache artifacts; use smaller scripts; implement retries with backoff; ensure storage performance tiers.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":109,\"element\":\"Terraform CLI -> Azure Resource Manager\",\"threat_description\":\"Compromised credentials allow attackers to tamper deployments and resources.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Least-privileged SPNs; MFA for operators; protect state; review plans; Azure Policy deny misconfigs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":110,\"element\":\"Terraform CLI -> Azure Resource Manager\",\"threat_description\":\"Provider/plan outputs can disclose sensitive IDs, names, or endpoints.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Mask sensitive outputs; secure state backend with RBAC and encryption; avoid outputting secrets.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":111,\"element\":\"Terraform CLI -> Azure Resource Manager\",\"threat_description\":\"High-frequency apply/plan cycles can hit ARM throttles, delaying legitimate changes.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Backoff on 429s; stagger pipelines; limit concurrency; monitor ARM quotas.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":112,\"element\":\"Terraform Operator Workstation -> Local files\",\"threat_description\":\"Local files containing secrets/configs can be tampered by local malware or users prior to zipping.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use secured build hosts; least privilege FS ACLs; integrity scan before packaging; ephemeral runners.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":113,\"element\":\"Terraform Operator Workstation -> Local files\",\"threat_description\":\"Secrets written to disk may be read by other processes or included in artifacts.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Avoid writing secrets; use secure temp stores; disk encryption; secret scanning in CI; .gitignore protections.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":114,\"element\":\"Terraform Operator Workstation -> Local files\",\"threat_description\":\"Large zips or repeated writes can lock the filesystem causing delays.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Limit artifact sizes; clean workspace; use CI runners with quotas.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":115,\"element\":\"azurerm_user_assigned_identity.user_id\",\"threat_description\":\"Identity credentials/tokens could be used to perform actions beyond intended scope if leaked.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Limit role to least privilege; use PIM; monitor token usage; Key Vault for secrets; private endpoints for Automation resources.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":116,\"element\":\"azurerm_user_assigned_identity.user_id\",\"threat_description\":\"Role bindings can be altered (tampered) to expand privileges unintentionally.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Protect role assignments with policy; change approvals; alerts on assignment changes; resource locks where sensible.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:N/SC:C/SI:H/SA:N\"},{\"id\":117,\"element\":\"azurerm_user_assigned_identity.user_id\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of audit on token issuance/usage can allow repudiation of performed actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable sign-in logs, conditionally require approvals, store logs immutably, correlate with runbook/job IDs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":118,\"element\":\"azurerm_user_assigned_identity.user_id\",\"threat_description\":\"Excessive use or token minting for long-lived sessions can be abused to throttle or lock processes (DoS).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Short token lifetimes; rate limit token issuance; revoke on anomalies; use PIM activation windows.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"}],\"is_final\":false}"
        },
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "**CONTINUE**"
        },
        {
            "role": "assistant",
            "content": "{\"message\":\"Continuing STRIDE-per-Element coverage. Adding remaining Process, Data Store, and Data Flow threats not yet enumerated, maintaining concise, non-duplicative items aligned to the described Terraform configuration. OWASP LLM and MITRE ATLAS remain not applicable (no LLM/ML), thus set to null.\",\"threats\":[{\"id\":119,\"element\":\"azurerm_app_service_plan.app_service_plan\",\"threat_description\":\"Attackers could spoof configuration references to bind additional apps to this plan, appearing as legitimate workloads.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Restrict who can create/update Function Apps and link to plans; use RBAC separation and Activity Log alerts on app-to-plan bindings.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":120,\"element\":\"azurerm_app_service_plan.app_service_plan\",\"threat_description\":\"Plan settings (SKU/scale limits) can be tampered to degrade performance or increase cost.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Policy-guard allowed SKUs; approval gates for scale changes; alerts on plan updates; resource locks where appropriate.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":121,\"element\":\"azurerm_app_service_plan.app_service_plan\",\"threat_description\":\"Insufficient auditing of plan changes leads to repudiation of who modified capacity/quotas.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable Activity Logs with retention; send to Log Analytics/immutable storage; require change tickets/justifications.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":122,\"element\":\"azurerm_app_service_plan.app_service_plan\",\"threat_description\":\"Plan metrics or diagnostics may disclose usage patterns and app names.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Limit who can read metrics; scrub sensitive tags; avoid exposing internal names in diagnostics visible to untrusted parties.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":123,\"element\":\"azurerm_app_service_plan.app_service_plan\",\"threat_description\":\"Misconfigured scale-out limits or quotas can deny service to hosted apps.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Set sane min/max limits; autoscale policies with safeguards; alerts on saturation; blue/green deploys.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":124,\"element\":\"azurerm_app_service_plan.app_service_plan\",\"threat_description\":\"Changing plan tier/features may unintentionally grant apps capabilities that broaden attack surface (e.g., enabling features not needed).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Deny non-approved SKUs via Policy; review effects of tier changes; least-privilege configurations at app level remain enforced.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":125,\"element\":\"data.archive_file.file_function_app\",\"threat_description\":\"Source path spoofing can cause unintended files to be included in the backend package.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use explicit include/ignore lists; verify package manifest; run on clean build agents only.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":126,\"element\":\"data.archive_file.file_function_app\",\"threat_description\":\"Packaged code can be tampered pre-zip to add backdoors.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Content signing; hash the artifact; restrict write access to source; SAST scans before packaging.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":127,\"element\":\"data.archive_file.file_function_app\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of provenance for artifacts enables repudiation of who built which package.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Generate SBOMs; sign artifacts (Sigstore); store build metadata immutably; enforce CI-only builds.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":128,\"element\":\"data.archive_file.file_function_app\",\"threat_description\":\"local.settings.json and secrets may be inadvertently included in the zip.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Exclude secret files; secret scanning; Key Vault references; separate config from code.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":129,\"element\":\"data.archive_file.file_function_app\",\"threat_description\":\"Very large archives can stall deployments or exhaust function storage.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Set size limits; prune dev dependencies; use CI caching and compression optimally; validate artifact size thresholds.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":130,\"element\":\"data.archive_file.file_function_app\",\"threat_description\":\"Injected post-install scripts or code-in-zip may execute with app permissions to broaden access.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"No post-install scripts in runtime; read-only package; integrity checks before mount; run as least-privileged identity.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":131,\"element\":\"data.archive_file.file_function_app_front\",\"threat_description\":\"Front-end archive path spoofing includes unintended/malicious assets.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Manifest-based packaging; restrict glob patterns; build in clean workspace.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":132,\"element\":\"data.archive_file.file_function_app_front\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampered JS/CSS can be packed to inject client-side malware/XSS.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Code signing/SRI; integrity gates in CI; static analysis; dependency pinning and SCA.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":133,\"element\":\"data.archive_file.file_function_app_front\",\"threat_description\":\"No artifact provenance allows repudiation of who published the frontend package.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Signed releases; Git tags with attestations; immutable artifact storage with approvals.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":134,\"element\":\"data.archive_file.file_function_app_front\",\"threat_description\":\"Source maps or env files in package may leak internal URLs/keys.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Strip source maps from prod; avoid embedding secrets; audit build outputs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":135,\"element\":\"data.archive_file.file_function_app_front\",\"threat_description\":\"Oversized bundles cause slow cold starts or deployment failures (DoS).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Bundle optimization; code splitting; enforce size budgets; CI checks.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":136,\"element\":\"data.archive_file.file_function_app_front\",\"threat_description\":\"Injected code leveraging front function permissions may access internal endpoints.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Run frontend function with minimal permissions; network egress controls; CSP and strict routing.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":137,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_replacement_upload\",\"threat_description\":\"Attacker could spoof backend hostname during replacement to route clients to malicious API.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Validate hostnames against allow-list; sign config files; review diffs in CI before publish.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:H/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":138,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_replacement_upload\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering with HTML/JS injection step can introduce XSS or backdoors.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Template integrity checks; content security policy; code review; automated DOM sanitization.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":139,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_replacement_upload\",\"threat_description\":\"No audit trail for file content changes enables repudiation of malicious edits.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Commit changes to VCS; signed commits; immutable logs with build job IDs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":140,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_replacement_upload\",\"threat_description\":\"Injected URLs may reveal internal endpoints or tokens if not sanitized.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Parameterize non-sensitive endpoints; never inject secrets into static assets; scanning for secrets in diffs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":141,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_replacement_upload\",\"threat_description\":\"Broken asset URLs or malformed bundles can take the frontend offline.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Static site tests; 404 fallbacks; deployment validation and canary releases.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":142,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_replacement_upload\",\"threat_description\":\"Injected code could call privileged admin APIs or escalate via stored credentials in code.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"No secrets in client code; enforce backend authorization; CSP to restrict external calls; review PRs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":143,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_replacement_vm_ip\",\"threat_description\":\"Replacing VM_IP_ADDR with attacker-controlled IP enables spoofed SSH targets.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Verify VM IP from trusted source; sign produced config.txt; distribute over private channel only.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:R/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":144,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_replacement_vm_ip\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering with SSH config options (ProxyCommand/Include) can introduce malicious command execution.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Template whitelisting; validate generated config against schema; avoid executing SSH config from untrusted storage.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":145,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_replacement_vm_ip\",\"threat_description\":\"Who modified the VM IP in the published file may be untraceable.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Immutable logs; signed artifacts; CI stamps in files (build ID, commit hash).\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":146,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_replacement_vm_ip\",\"threat_description\":\"Publishing VM IP to public storage leaks target information for attackers.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Do not publish; keep file private; rotate IPs; restrict SSH exposure and enforce key auth.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":147,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_replacement_vm_ip\",\"threat_description\":\"Bad replacement may break automation/SSH access (operational DoS).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Validation tests; fallback configs; change control with rollbacks.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":148,\"element\":\"null_resource.file_replacement_vm_ip\",\"threat_description\":\"Manipulated config may execute commands on client machines (EoP on operator hosts).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Avoid distributing executable SSH configs; sanitize options; least-privileged operator accounts; code review.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":149,\"element\":\"azurerm_public_ip.VM_PublicIP\",\"threat_description\":\"DNS label confusion may allow spoofed endpoints similar to expected hostname.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use custom domains with TLS certificates; publish fingerprints; advise SSH StrictHostKeyChecking.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:M/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":150,\"element\":\"azurerm_public_ip.VM_PublicIP\",\"threat_description\":\"Public IP or DNS label can be tampered to point clients to unintended targets.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"RBAC restrict updates; resource locks; alerts on IP/DNS changes; use static IP if feasible.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":151,\"element\":\"azurerm_public_ip.VM_PublicIP\",\"threat_description\":\"Insufficient auditing of IP/DNS updates allows repudiation.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Activity Logs with retention; change approvals; immutable logging.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":152,\"element\":\"azurerm_public_ip.VM_PublicIP\",\"threat_description\":\"Public IP exposure reveals target for scanning and exploitation.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"JIT access; restrict NSG; do not publish IP; use bastion/privileged access workstations.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":153,\"element\":\"azurerm_public_ip.VM_PublicIP\",\"threat_description\":\"Volumetric attacks against the IP or frequent reassignment can cause outages.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"DDoS Protection Standard; rate-limit SSH; consider Azure Bastion with private VMs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":154,\"element\":\"azurerm_public_ip.VM_PublicIP\",\"threat_description\":\"If IP is used as trust anchor, control over it could allow lateral access (e.g., IP-based allow lists).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Avoid IP-based trust; use identity-aware access; verify source identities at app layer.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":155,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_public_ip.vm_ip\",\"threat_description\":\"Reading the wrong subscription/context can spoof the returned VM IP.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Pin provider tenant/subscription; assert resource IDs; validate against NIC properties.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":156,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_public_ip.vm_ip\",\"threat_description\":\"Local tampering of state or data source config can cause incorrect IP to be propagated.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Protect state with RBAC and encryption; code reviews; drift detection.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":157,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_public_ip.vm_ip\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of logging of data source evaluations hinders attribution.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable TF detailed logs stored securely; include plan/apply artifacts in change records.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":158,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_public_ip.vm_ip\",\"threat_description\":\"Emitting the IP to files/logs discloses target address.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Mask IPs in public logs; avoid publishing to public storage; restrict read access to artifacts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":159,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_public_ip.vm_ip\",\"threat_description\":\"Repeated queries during deploy may hit API limits delaying provisioning.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Cache values; query once at apply; use retries/backoff.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":160,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_public_ip.vm_ip\",\"threat_description\":\"Propagating an attacker-controlled IP into configs may enable further pivoting.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Cross-validate IP with resource graph; sign and verify generated configs; restrict write to public locations.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:R/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":161,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_interface.net_int\",\"threat_description\":\"NIC association spoofing or confusion can attach the wrong NIC to the VM.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use explicit resource IDs; RBAC restrict NIC attach/detach; approvals for NIC changes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":162,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_interface.net_int\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering NIC IP config/NSG association can expose services or break segmentation.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Policy enforce subnets/NSG; alerts on NIC config changes; change control.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":163,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_interface.net_int\",\"threat_description\":\"Who altered NIC settings may be untraceable without logs.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Activity Logs and Resource Graph change history to SIEM; immutable retention.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":164,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_interface.net_int\",\"threat_description\":\"NIC metadata reveals private IPs and topology details.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"RBAC limit read to network metadata; avoid exposing outputs; sanitize diagnostics.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":165,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_interface.net_int\",\"threat_description\":\"Misconfiguration or detach can cut network connectivity (DoS).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Resource locks; change approvals; validation tests; redundant NICs if supported.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":166,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_interface.net_int\",\"threat_description\":\"Attaching NIC to unintended subnet may allow lateral movement and broader access.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Subnet/NSG bindings enforced by Policy; least-privilege RBAC; continuous compliance scans.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":167,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_interface_security_group_association.example\",\"threat_description\":\"Spoof association to bind a permissive NSG to the NIC.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Validate NSG IDs; policy deny bindings to non-approved NSGs; RBAC separation for network/security roles.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":168,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_interface_security_group_association.example\",\"threat_description\":\"Association tampering can open ports or remove protections.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Policy guardrails; alerts on NSG association changes; resource locks.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":169,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_interface_security_group_association.example\",\"threat_description\":\"Without logging, changes to the association can be repudiated.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Activity logs and NSG flow logs to SIEM; change tickets required for security rule updates.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":170,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_interface_security_group_association.example\",\"threat_description\":\"Association metadata may disclose security posture and open ports to observers with read access.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Limit read permissions; avoid exporting rule details broadly; sanitize documentation.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":171,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_interface_security_group_association.example\",\"threat_description\":\"Removal or swap of NSG could expose NIC to attack, causing service outage or compromise.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Policy: NSG required; CI checks; automatic remediation; alert on disassociation.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":172,\"element\":\"azurerm_network_interface_security_group_association.example\",\"threat_description\":\"Binding to an NSG that allows management endpoints may enable privilege escalation via reachable services.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Approved NSG catalog; deny rules for management ports from internet; peer review on security changes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":173,\"element\":\"azurerm_virtual_machine_extension.test\",\"threat_description\":\"Spoofing extension publisher/type enables execution of untrusted code as root.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Pin publisher/type/version; allow-list extensions; verify package signatures/hashes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":174,\"element\":\"azurerm_virtual_machine_extension.test\",\"threat_description\":\"Script/command tampering in protectedSettings/publicSettings can alter actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Template integrity; store scripts privately; verify checksums; avoid inline scripts when possible.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:M\"},{\"id\":175,\"element\":\"azurerm_virtual_machine_extension.test\",\"threat_description\":\"Insufficient job logs/signatures allow repudiation of actions performed by the extension.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable extension logs collection to LA; sign scripts; correlate with deployment IDs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":176,\"element\":\"azurerm_virtual_machine_extension.test\",\"threat_description\":\"Extension may log secrets or include SAS URLs in cleartext.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Mask logs; avoid secrets in parameters/URLs; use MSI to fetch artifacts; store secrets in Key Vault.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":177,\"element\":\"azurerm_virtual_machine_extension.test\",\"threat_description\":\"Failed or looping extension can block provisioning or consume resources.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Set timeouts/retries; idempotent scripts; monitor provisioning state; break-glass disable path.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":178,\"element\":\"azurerm_virtual_machine_extension.test\",\"threat_description\":\"Extension runs with high privileges on VM, enabling full takeover if compromised.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Minimize extension use; run least-privileged actions; isolate secrets; verify integrity before execution; lock down IMDS access.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:C/SI:H/SA:M\"},{\"id\":179,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_subscription.primary\",\"threat_description\":\"Misconfigured provider context can spoof subscription targeting, applying to the wrong tenant/subscription.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Hardcode subscription/tenant IDs; environment protections; pre-apply guardrails validating target subscription.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":180,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_subscription.primary\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering provider config or TF variables can redirect operations to unintended scopes.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use workspace-scoped variables; OPA/Conftest policy checks; code review; signed TF vars.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":181,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_subscription.primary\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of recorded context during plan/apply leads to repudiation of targeted subscription.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Capture TF logs/state metadata; store commit SHA and subscription ID with plan artifacts in immutable storage.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":182,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_subscription.primary\",\"threat_description\":\"Subscription IDs/names in logs may disclose organizational structure.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Mask IDs in public channels; limit who can read pipeline logs; rotate display names where sensitive.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":183,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_subscription.primary\",\"threat_description\":\"Overuse of management APIs during discovery can hit throttles.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Cache subscription data; minimal reads; backoff on 429; stagger environments.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":184,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_subscription.primary\",\"threat_description\":\"Knowledge of subscription scope combined with broad credentials can aid escalation across RGs.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Least-privilege roles; PIM; policy deny at management group; break-glass controls monitored.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":185,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_client_config.example\",\"threat_description\":\"Spoofed client/tenant context can mislead deployments or leak metadata.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Assert tenant/client IDs from secure variables; verify using MS Graph; CI guardrails.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":186,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_client_config.example\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering with environment credentials (AZURE_* vars) can redirect actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Ephemeral CI identities; sealed secrets; validate audience/issuer on tokens; minimal env exposure.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":187,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_client_config.example\",\"threat_description\":\"Insufficient logging of client config usage leads to repudiation.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Record client object IDs and correlation IDs in build logs; immutable retention.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":188,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_client_config.example\",\"threat_description\":\"Exposing tenant/client IDs publicly aids reconnaissance.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Avoid printing IDs to logs; use masked variables; restrict pipeline log access.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":189,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_client_config.example\",\"threat_description\":\"Frequent metadata calls can contribute to throttling issues.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Cache client metadata; call once per run; handle 429 with backoff.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":190,\"element\":\"data.azurerm_client_config.example\",\"threat_description\":\"Knowledge of client principal combined with leaked credentials aids privilege escalation.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Rotate credentials; workload identity federation; scoped permissions; PIM for admin roles.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":191,\"element\":\"azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_vm (Contributor at RG)\",\"threat_description\":\"VM MSI could be spoofed by processes on the VM to obtain tokens and act as the VM identity.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Constrain IMDS access (firewall/iptables); MSI endpoint protection; app allow-list for token requests; least-privilege role (not Contributor).\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":192,\"element\":\"azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_vm (Contributor at RG)\",\"threat_description\":\"Role scope can be tampered to broaden to subscription or add additional privileges.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Azure Policy deny on high-scope role assignments; approval workflows; alerts on role changes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:N/SC:C/SI:H/SA:N\"},{\"id\":193,\"element\":\"azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_vm (Contributor at RG)\",\"threat_description\":\"Without logging/access reviews, actions by the VM identity may be repudiated.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"PIM/Azure AD sign-in logs; correlate token use with VM; Log Analytics for ARM operations by principal.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":194,\"element\":\"azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_vm (Contributor at RG)\",\"threat_description\":\"Contributor read permissions may expose resource data and configurations beyond necessity.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Custom least-privilege roles; deny data-plane access; segment RGs; restrict who can read app settings/secrets.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":195,\"element\":\"azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_vm (Contributor at RG)\",\"threat_description\":\"Contributor identity can delete/update resources causing outages.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Reduce to specific roles; resource locks; approvals for destructive actions; alert on deletes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":196,\"element\":\"azurerm_role_assignment.az_role_assgn_vm (Contributor at RG)\",\"threat_description\":\"Contributor enables lateral movement (create role assignments for others, manipulate networking) leading to EoP.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Remove role assignment; if needed, use custom role without roleAssignment write; continuous compliance checks.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:C/SI:H/SA:M\"},{\"id\":197,\"element\":\"null_resource.clientid_replacement\",\"threat_description\":\"Client ID/RG name replacement can be spoofed to inject attacker-controlled identity references.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Validate against Azure AD/ARM before substitution; sign templates; review diffs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:R/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":198,\"element\":\"null_resource.clientid_replacement\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering with runbook parameters can cause it to act on unintended resources.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Schema validation; least-privilege runbooks; parameter allow-lists; code review.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:R/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":199,\"element\":\"null_resource.clientid_replacement\",\"threat_description\":\"No audit of substitutions allows repudiation of who changed runbook identifiers.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Record substitution logs with commit/build IDs; immutable storage; approvals.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":200,\"element\":\"null_resource.clientid_replacement\",\"threat_description\":\"Embedding client IDs may disclose tenant structure and principal GUIDs.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Avoid publishing scripts containing IDs; scope access; mask in logs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":201,\"element\":\"null_resource.clientid_replacement\",\"threat_description\":\"Bad substitutions can break automation or cause runaway jobs (DoS).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Pre-run validation; sandbox testing; retries with backoff; circuit breakers.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":202,\"element\":\"null_resource.clientid_replacement\",\"threat_description\":\"Substituting elevated identity references can grant runbooks excessive power.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use fixed UAMI with least privilege; deny changes to identity references via Policy; peer review.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":203,\"element\":\"data.local_file.runbook_file\",\"threat_description\":\"Runbook file content can be modified before upload to perform unintended actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Content hashing; signed scripts; store in secured repo; limit local write access.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":204,\"element\":\"data.local_file.runbook_file\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of versioning/provenance may allow repudiation of script changes.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Version control; immutable artifact storage; signed commits with attestations.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":205,\"element\":\"data.local_file.runbook_file\",\"threat_description\":\"File may contain client IDs/secrets or sensitive resource names.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Remove secrets; parameterize via Key Vault; restrict file permissions; secret scanning.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":206,\"element\":\"data.local_file.runbook_file\",\"threat_description\":\"Large or malformed script content can fail uploads or executions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Size and syntax checks; unit tests; CI gates; chunked uploads with retry.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":207,\"element\":\"azurerm_automation_runbook.dev_automation_runbook\",\"threat_description\":\"Spoofed parameters or caller context can make runbook act on unintended targets.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Require authenticated calls with AAD; validate parameters; restrict Start-Runbook permissions.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:R/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":208,\"element\":\"azurerm_automation_runbook.dev_automation_runbook\",\"threat_description\":\"Runbook content can be tampered to perform destructive or exfiltrative actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Signed runbooks; approvals and peer review; content scanning; restrict who can edit/publish.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:C/SI:H/SA:M\"},{\"id\":209,\"element\":\"azurerm_automation_runbook.dev_automation_runbook\",\"threat_description\":\"Insufficient job/stream logging allows repudiation of actions run by the runbook.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable verbose/progress logs to Log Analytics; immutable retention; correlate with identity and schedule IDs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":210,\"element\":\"azurerm_automation_runbook.dev_automation_runbook\",\"threat_description\":\"Runbook may print secrets or resource metadata to logs.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use secure variables/assets; mask outputs; never log tokens; Key Vault integration.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":211,\"element\":\"azurerm_automation_runbook.dev_automation_runbook\",\"threat_description\":\"Misconfigured schedules/loops can consume Automation capacity and block legitimate jobs.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Concurrency limits; timeouts; job quotas; alerts on long-running jobs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":212,\"element\":\"azurerm_automation_runbook.dev_automation_runbook\",\"threat_description\":\"With UAMI Owner, a compromised runbook enables full RG takeover (EoP).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Replace Owner with least-privilege custom role; PIM; split duties; approval for privileged jobs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:C/SI:H/SA:H\"},{\"id\":213,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.app_files_prod\",\"threat_description\":\"If credentials or SAS leak, production static files can be tampered.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Private container; RBAC with MSI; blob immutability/versioning; CI-only writes; rotate keys/SAS.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":214,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.app_files_prod\",\"threat_description\":\"Attribution of changes may be weak if using ad-hoc SAS without identifiers.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Stored access policies with signedIdentifier; diagnostic logging; immutable retention.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":215,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.app_files_prod\",\"threat_description\":\"Publicly reachable blobs (if path known) may reveal sensitive asset metadata or configuration embedded in files.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Serve via CDN with signed URLs; remove sensitive data from static assets; set container to private.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":216,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.app_files_prod\",\"threat_description\":\"High-volume downloads of static assets can drive egress cost or throttle origin.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Front with CDN/WAF and caching; rate limiting; monitor egress and create alerts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":217,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.config_update_prod\",\"threat_description\":\"If blob path is guessed and write creds leak, attacker can replace config file contents.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Make container private; immutability policies; ensure no secrets or live endpoints inside; rotate SAS/keys.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":218,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.config_update_prod\",\"threat_description\":\"Changes via SAS without identifiers hinder attribution.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use stored access policies; logging; correlate with deployment IDs; immutable retention.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":219,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.config_update_prod\",\"threat_description\":\"If accessed, the file could disclose IPs/paths or environment details.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Do not store sensitive details; move to private container; encryption at rest and access logging.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":220,\"element\":\"azurerm_storage_blob.config_update_prod\",\"threat_description\":\"Excessive reads or hot access patterns can throttle blob service.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"CDN caching; rate limits; monitor for anomalies; rotate URLs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":221,\"element\":\"random_id.randomId\",\"threat_description\":\"Predictable random IDs could allow spoofing of resource names and collisions.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use cryptographically strong randomness; sufficient length; avoid exposing seeds; do not rely on secrecy of names.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":222,\"element\":\"random_id.randomId\",\"threat_description\":\"Local environment tampering might influence seed/state to produce chosen IDs.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Lock state remotely with encryption and RBAC; run in controlled CI; verify entropy source.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":223,\"element\":\"random_id.randomId\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of traceability of ID generation can be repudiated.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Record generated IDs with commit/build IDs; immutable logs; deterministic naming where possible.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":224,\"element\":\"random_id.randomId\",\"threat_description\":\"Generated IDs in logs may reveal resource patterns that aid reconnaissance.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Limit log exposure; avoid including IDs in public artifacts; rotate naming schemes if leaked.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":225,\"element\":\"random_id.randomId\",\"threat_description\":\"Excessive generation attempts could slow plan/apply.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Avoid loops; cache IDs; generate once and reuse.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":226,\"element\":\"random_id.randomId\",\"threat_description\":\"Names based on predictable IDs could allow attackers to pre-create resources and hijack flows.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use provider-side uniqueness checks; randomize with sufficient entropy; verify resource existence before naming.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:M/VA:N/SC:C/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":227,\"element\":\"Locals (SAS/now/date formatting)\",\"threat_description\":\"Spoofed or manipulated input values could yield incorrect times or identifiers used in SAS generation.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Compute SAS server-side with secure time sources; do not rely on local time; validate ranges.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:M/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":228,\"element\":\"Locals (SAS/now/date formatting)\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering locals can create overlong SAS TTLs or excess privileges.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Hard cap TTLs; enforce permissions server-side; policies denying long-lived SAS.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":229,\"element\":\"Locals (SAS/now/date formatting)\",\"threat_description\":\"No record of local value derivation can be repudiated when incidents occur.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Log computed values and inputs securely; include in build artifacts with signatures.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":230,\"element\":\"Locals (SAS/now/date formatting)\",\"threat_description\":\"Computed values may leak sensitive timing/windows (validity periods) that aid attackers.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Avoid exposing SAS validity; rotate often; use server-side generation with opaque tokens.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":231,\"element\":\"Locals (SAS/now/date formatting)\",\"threat_description\":\"Bad date math can invalidate tokens or cause deployment failures (DoS).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Unit tests for time calculations; timezone consistency; fail-safe defaults.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":232,\"element\":\"Locals (SAS/now/date formatting)\",\"threat_description\":\"Over-privileged SAS computed in locals can grant excessive rights to consuming services.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Generate least-privilege SAS server-side; prefer MSI + RBAC over SAS entirely.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":233,\"element\":\"Terraform Operator Workstation -> Cosmos DB\",\"threat_description\":\"Seeding scripts can tamper with data (wrong endpoint/key or compromised host).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use MSI + AAD with scoped permissions; verify endpoint; run from trusted CI; code reviews of seed scripts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":234,\"element\":\"Terraform Operator Workstation -> Cosmos DB\",\"threat_description\":\"Cosmos endpoint/key may be exposed in local logs or memory during operations.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Mask secrets; avoid writing to disk; use Key Vault-backed creds; rotate keys; private endpoints.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":235,\"element\":\"Terraform Operator Workstation -> Cosmos DB\",\"threat_description\":\"Bulk operations or retries may cause RU throttling or service degradation.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Batch writes; respect RU budgets; backoff with jitter; pre-provision throughput for initial load.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":236,\"element\":\"Terraform Operator Workstation -> Storage Account\",\"threat_description\":\"Using account keys/connection strings, operator can tamper with any blob/container.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use MSI + RBAC; per-container roles; avoid account keys; enable versioning/immutability.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:N/SC:C/SI:H/SA:N\"},{\"id\":237,\"element\":\"Terraform Operator Workstation -> Storage Account\",\"threat_description\":\"Keys/SAS may leak in CLI output or referrers during uploads.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use HTTPS; scrub logs; never embed SAS in URLs visible to public; short TTL; IP restrictions.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:L/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":238,\"element\":\"Terraform Operator Workstation -> Storage Account\",\"threat_description\":\"Bulk uploads may cause throttling or cost spikes.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Parallelism limits; exponential backoff; CDN for distribution; monitor transactions.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":239,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app_front -> Storage Account (package SAS)\",\"threat_description\":\"If SAS is over-privileged, the function could modify container contents (tampering) during fetch or via SSRF.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use read-only SAS; shortest TTL; store packages in private containers accessible via MSI; verify blob version IDs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:M/VA:N/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":240,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app_front -> Storage Account (package SAS)\",\"threat_description\":\"Blob SAS in app settings/requests could be exposed to attackers or logs.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Key Vault references; do not log environment; rotate SAS often; avoid embedding SAS in connection strings.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:M/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":241,\"element\":\"azurerm_function_app.function_app_front -> Storage Account (package SAS)\",\"threat_description\":\"Repeated blob fetches during cold starts or attack traffic can throttle storage.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable warm starts; local caching; CDN; restrict SAS scope; monitor storage throttling metrics.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":242,\"element\":\"Azure Automation Runbook -> Azure Resource Manager\",\"threat_description\":\"Runbook actions can tamper resources at RG scope using Owner UAMI.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Reduce role; approval-based execution; Policy deny for destructive actions; just-in-time elevation via PIM.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:N/SC:C/SI:H/SA:N\"},{\"id\":243,\"element\":\"Azure Automation Runbook -> Azure Resource Manager\",\"threat_description\":\"Runbook may read sensitive configurations and output them, causing data exposure.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Mask outputs; limit Get operations; Key Vault access restrictions; logging with sensitive data filtering.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:C/SI:M/SA:N\"},{\"id\":244,\"element\":\"Azure Automation Runbook -> Azure Resource Manager\",\"threat_description\":\"Aggressive runbook operations can hit ARM throttles, delaying legitimate management operations.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Backoff/retry; schedule off-peak; limit concurrency; monitor 429s and operation latency.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:M/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":245,\"element\":\"Terraform data source -> Public IP service\",\"threat_description\":\"If queries are intercepted/modified, returned IP could be tampered with (confused deputy).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use ARM API over TLS; verify resource IDs; avoid third-party IP services; validate against NIC binding.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":246,\"element\":\"Terraform data source -> Public IP service\",\"threat_description\":\"Returned IPs may be written to public artifacts, disclosing infrastructure endpoints.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Avoid publishing IPs; mask in logs; restrict artifact access; private distribution only.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":247,\"element\":\"Terraform data source -> Public IP service\",\"threat_description\":\"Excessive polling for assigned IP can contribute to API rate limits (DoS).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Poll with backoff; rely on ARM events; cache results; limit retries.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"}],\"is_final\":true}"
        }
    ]
}